(14001, 'lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'No meaningful clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when lisinopril was used concomitantly with propranolol, digoxin, or hydrochlorothiazide. It is recommended that serum lithium levels be monitored frequently if lisinopril is administered concomitantly with lithium.Hydrochlorothiazide: When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics.Alcohol, Barbiturates, Or Narcotics— potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur.Antidiabetic Drugs (Oral Agents And Insulin) — dosage adjustment of the antidiabetic drug may be required.Other Antihypertensive Drugs — additive effect or potentiation.Cholestyramine And Colestipol Resins — Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins. Single doses of ei', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Acute renal failure has been reported in a few patients receiving indomethacin and formulations containing triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide. Caution is therefore advised when administering nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory agents with triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'doxazosin mesylate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Doxazosin mesylate tablets have been used with the following drugs or drug classes: 1) analgesic/anti-inflammatory (e.g., acetaminophen, aspirin, codeine and codeine combinations, ibuprofen, indomethacin); 2) antibiotics (e.g., erythromycin, trimethoprim and sulfamethoxazole, amoxicillin); 3) antihistamines (e.g., chlorpheniramine); 4) cardiovascular agents (e.g., atenolol, hydrochlorothiazide, propranolol); 5) corticosteroids; 6) gastrointestinal agents (e.g., antacids); 7) hypoglycemics and endocrine drugs; 8) sedatives and tranquilizers (e.g., diazepam); 9) cold and flu remedies.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'benazepril hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'major', 'Other No clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when benazepril hydrochloride tablets were administered concomitantly with hydrochlorothiazide, chlorthalidone, furosemide, digoxin, propranolol, atenolol, naproxen, or cimetidine.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'fosinopril sodium and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions Potassium supplements and potassium-sparing diuretics: As noted above ("Derangements of Serum Electrolytes"), the net effect of fosinopril sodium and hydrochlorothiazide may be to elevate a patient''s serum potassium, to reduce it, or to leave it unchanged. Because renal clearance of lithium is reduced by thiazides, the risk of lithium toxicity is presumably raised further when, as in therapy with fosinopril sodium and hydrochlorothiazide tablets, a thiazide diuretic is coadministered with the ACE inhibitor. Other ACE inhibitors have had less than additive effects with betaadrenergic blockers, presumably because drugs of both classes lower blood pressure by inhibiting parts of the renin-angiotensin system.Interaction studies with warfarin have failed to identify any clinic', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'quinapril', 'N/A', 'minor', 'No pharmacokinetic interaction was observed when single doses of quinapril hydrochloride andhydrochlorothiazide were administered concomitantly.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'lisinopril', 'N/A', 'major', 'No clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when lisinopril was used concomitantly with propranolol or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'terazosin hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Terazosin has been used concomitantly in at least 50 patients on the following drugs or drug classes: 1) analgesic/anti-inflammatory (e.g., acetaminophen, aspirin, codeine, ibuprofen, indomethacin); 2) antibiotics (e.g., erythromycin, trimethoprim and sulfamethoxazole); 3) anticholinergic/sympathomimetics (e.g., phenylephrine hydrochloride, phenylpropanolamine hydrochloride, pseudoephedrine hydrochloride); 4) antigout (e.g., allopurinol); 5) antihistamines (e.g., chlorpheniramine); 6) cardiovascular agents (e.g., atenolol, hydrochlorothiazide, methyclothiazide, propranolol); 7) corticosteroids; 8) gastrointestinal agents (e.g., antacids); 9) hypoglycemics; 10) sedatives and tranquilizers (e.g., diazepam).', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'drug_class', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions When given concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'irbesartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '[See Clinical Pharmacology (12.3).] Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, Barbiturates, or Narcotics: potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and Colestipol Resins: absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins. Single doses of either cholestyramine or colestipol resins bind the hydrochlorothiazide and reduce its absorption from the gastrointestinal tract by up to 85% and 43%, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'carvedilol phosphate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide A single oral dose of carvedilol 25 mg did not alter the pharmacokinetics of a single oral dose of hydrochlorothiazide 25 mg in 12 patients with hypertension. Likewise, hydrochlorothiazide had no effect on the pharmacokinetics of carvedilol.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'colestipol hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'major', 'The absorption of tetracycline, furosemide, penicillin G, hydrochlorothiazide, and gemfibrozil was significantly decreased when given simultaneously with colestipol hydrochloride; these drugs were not tested to determine the effect of administration one hour before colestipol hydrochloride.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'aliskiren hemifumarate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No drug interaction studies have been conducted with Tekturna HCT and other drugs, although studies with the individual aliskiren and hydrochlorothiazide components are described below. Drugs with no clinically significant effects: Coadministration of lovastatin, atenolol, warfarin, furosemide, digoxin, celecoxib, hydrochlorothiazide, ramipril, valsartan, metformin and amlodipine did not result in clinically significant increases in aliskiren exposure. Drugs with no clinically significant effects: Coadministration of aliskiren did not significantly affect the pharmacokinetics of lovastatin, digoxin, valsartan, amlodipine, metformin, celecoxib, atenolol, atorvastatin, ramipril or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'etodolac', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Diuretics Etodolac has no apparent pharmacokinetic interaction when administered with furosemide or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'amantadine hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Coadministration of Dyazide (triamterene/hydrochlorothiazide) resulted in a higher plasma amantadine concentration in a 61-year-old man receiving amantadine 100 mg TID for Parkinson''s disease.1 It is not known which of the components of Dyazide contributed to the observation or if related drugs produce a similar response.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'enalapril maleate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics – potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins – Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins. Single doses of either cholestyramine or colestipol resins bind the hydrochlorothiazide and reduce its absorption from the gastrointestinal tract by up to 85 and 43 percent, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'ketoprofen', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide, given concomitantly with ketoprofen, produces a reduction in urinary potassium and chloride excretion compared to hydrochlorothiazide alone.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'febuxostat', 'N/A', 'major', '7.3 In Vivo Drug Interaction Studies Based on drug interaction studies in healthy subjects, ULORIC does not have clinically significant interactions with colchicine, naproxen, indomethacin, hydrochlorothiazide, warfarin or desipramine [see Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)].', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'pramipexole dihydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Other drugs eliminated via renal secretion: Population pharmacokinetic analysis suggests that coadministration of drugs that are secreted by the cationic transport system (e.g., cimetidine, ranitidine, diltiazem, triamterene, verapamil, quinidine, and quinine) decreases the oral clearance of pramipexole by about 20%, while those secreted by the anionic transport system (e.g., cephalosporins, penicillins, indomethacin, hydrochlorothiazide, and chlorpropamide) are likely to have little effect on the oral clearance of pramipexole.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'losartan potassium and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'There is no pharmacokinetic interaction between losartan and hydrochlorothiazide. Hydrochlorothiazide After oral administration of hydrochlorothiazide, diuresis begins within 2 hours, peaks in about 4 hours and lasts about 6 to 12 hours. Hydrochlorothiazide is not metabolized but is eliminated rapidly by the kidney.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'topiramate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide (HCTZ): A drug-drug interaction study conducted in healthy volunteers evaluated the steady-state pharmacokinetics of HCTZ (25 mg q24h) and topiramate (96 mg q12h) when administered alone and concomitantly.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'valsartan', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when Diovan (valsartan) was coadministered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'lisinopril, arginine', 'N/A', 'major', 'No clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when Lisinopril Tablets were used concomitantly with propranolol or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'losartan potassium', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions No significant drug-drug pharmacokinetic interactions have been found in interaction studies with hydrochlorothiazide, digoxin, warfarin, cimetidine and phenobarbital.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'milrinone lactate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions No untoward clinical manifestations have been observed in limited experience with patients in whom milrinone was used concurrently with the following drugs: digitalis glycosides; lidocaine, quinidine; hydralazine, prazosin; isosorbide dinitrate, nitroglycerin; chlorthalidone, furosemide, hydrochlorothiazide, spironolactone; captopril; heparin, warfarin, diazepam, insulin; and potassium supplements.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'irbesartan', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions No significant drug-drug pharmacokinetic (or pharmacodynamic) interactions have been found in interaction studies with hydrochlorothiazide, digoxin, warfarin, and nifedipine. In separate studies of patients receiving maintenance doses of warfarin, hydrochlorothiazide, or digoxin, irbesartan administration for 7 days had no effect on the pharmacodynamics of warfarin (prothrombin time) or pharmacokinetics of digoxin. The pharmacokinetics of irbesartan were not affected by coadministration of nifedipine or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'amlodipine valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'Valsartan No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was co-administered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin. Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics: Potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins: Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'eprosartan mesylate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Or 800 mg q.d.) doses have been safely used concomitantly with a thiazide diuretic (hydrochlorothiazide). Hydrochlorothiazide: When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics – potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins – Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Valsartan: No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was coadministered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin. Hydrochlorothiazide: When administered concurrently, the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, Barbiturates, or N arcotics - Potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and Colestipol R esins - Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'amlodipine besylate and valsartan', 'N/A', 'major', 'Studies with Valsartan No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was co-administered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'acebutolol hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'major', 'No significant interactions with digoxin, hydrochlorothiazide, hydralazine, sulfinpyrazone, oral contraceptives, tolbutamide, or warfarin have been observed.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'candesartan cilexetil and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions Candesartan Cilexetil No significant drug interactions have been reported in studies of candesartan cilexetil given with other drugs such as glyburide, nifedipine, digoxin, warfarin, hydrochlorothiazide, and oral contraceptives in healthy volunteers. Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics − Potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins − Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'telmisartan', 'N/A', 'major', 'Other Drugs: Co-administration of telmisartan did not result in a clinically significant interaction with acetaminophen, amlodipine, glyburide, simvastatin, hydrochlorothiazide, warfarin, or ibuprofen.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'telmisartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'Because lithium should not be used with diuretics, the use of lithium with telmisartan and hydrochlorothiazide is not recommended. Other Drugs: Co-administration of telmisartan did not result in a clinically significant interaction with acetaminophen, amlodipine, glibenclamide, simvastatin, hydrochlorothiazide or ibuprofen. Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently, the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics: Potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'benazepril hydrochloride and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Cholestyramine and colestipol resins: Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins. Single doses of either cholestyramine or colestipol resins bind the hydrochlorothiazide and reduce its absorption from the gastrointestinal tract by up to 85% and 43%, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'betaxolol', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions The following drugs have been coadministered with betaxolol and have not altered its pharmacokinetics: cimetidine, nifedipine, chlorthalidone, and hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'fluconazole', 'N/A', 'contraindicated', 'These are described in greater detail below: Oral hypoglycemics Coumarin-type anticoagulants Phenytoin Cyclosporine Rifampin Theophylline Terfenadine Cisapride Astemizole Rifabutin Voriconazole Tacrolimus Short-acting benzodiazepines Triazolam Oral Contraceptives Pimozide Hydrochlorothiazide Alfentanil Amitriptyline, nortriptyline Amphotericin B Azithromycin Carbamazepine Calcium Channel Blockers Celecoxib Cyclophosphamide Fentanyl Halofantrine HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors Losartan Methadone Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs Prednisone Saquinavir Sirolimus Vinca Alkaloids Vitamin A Zidovudine Oral hypoglycemics: Clinically significant hypoglycemia may be precipitated by the use of fluconazole with oral hypoglycemic agents; one fatality has been reported from hypoglycemia in association', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'fosinopril sodium', 'N/A', 'minor', 'In separate single or multiple dose pharmacokinetic interaction studies with chlorthalidone, nifedipine, propranolol, hydrochlorothiazide, cimetidine, metoclopramide, propantheline, digoxin, and warfarin, the bioavailability of fosinoprilat was not altered by coadministration of fosinopril with any one of these drugs.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'candesartan cilexetil', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No significant drug interactions have been reported in studies of candesartan cilexetil given with other drugs such as glyburide, nifedipine, digoxin, warfarin, hydrochlorothiazide, and oral contraceptives in healthy volunteers, or given with enalapril to patients with heart failure (NYHA class II and III).', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'losartan potatssium', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions No significant drug-drug pharmacokinetic interactions have been found in interaction studies with hydrochlorothiazide, digoxin, warfarin, cimetidine and phenobarbital.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'terazosin', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Terazosin has been used concomitantly in at least 50 patients on the following drugs or drug classes: 1) analgesic/anti-inflammatory (e.g., acetaminophen, aspirin, codeine, ibuprofen, indomethacin); 2) antibiotics (e.g., erythromycin, trimethoprim and sulfamethoxazole); 3) anticholinergic/sympathomimetics (e.g., phenylephrine hydrochloride, phenylpropanolamine hydrochloride, pseudoephedrine hydrochloride); 4) antigout (e.g., allopurinol); 5) antihistamines (e.g., chlorpheniramine); 6) cardiovascular agents (e.g., atenolol, hydrochlorothiazide, methyclothiazide, propranolol); 7) corticosteroids; 8) gastrointestinal agents (e.g., antacids); 9) hypoglycemics; 10) sedatives and tranquilizers (e.g., diazepam).', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'carbamazepine', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Concomitant medication with carbamazepine and some diuretics (hydrochlorothiazide, furosemide) may lead to symptomatic hyponatremia.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'quinapril hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'No pharmacokinetic interaction was observed when single doses of quinapril hydrochloride and hydrochlorothiazide were administered concomitantly.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'isradipine', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Nitroglycerin: A study in normal healthy volunteers has shown that concomitant administration of isradipine and hydrochlorothiazide does not result in altered pharmacokinetics of either drug. In a study in hypertensive patients, addition of isradipine to existing hydrochlorothiazide therapy did not result in any unexpected adverse effects, and isradipine had an additional antihypertensive effect. Hydrochlorothiazide: In a single dose study in normal volunteers, co-administration of propranolol had a small effect on the rate but no effect on the extent of isradipine bioavailability.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'amlodipine and valsartan', 'N/A', 'major', 'Studies with Valsartan No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was co-administered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'quinapril hydrochloride and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Drug Interactions Agents Increasing Serum Potassium: Coadministration of quinapril HCl and hydrochlorothiazide tablets with other drugs that raise serum potassium levels may result in hyperkalemia. Because renal clearance of lithium is reduced by thiazides, the risk of lithium toxicity is presumably raised further when, as in therapy with quinapril HCl and hydrochlorothiazide tablets, a thiazide diuretic is coadministered with the ACE inhibitor. Quinapril HCl and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and lithium should be coadministered with caution, and frequent monitoring of serum lithium levels is recommended.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'memantine hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', '7.4 Drugs Eliminated via Renal Mechanisms Because memantine is eliminated in part by tubular secretion, coadministration of drugs that use the same renal cationic system, including hydrochlorothiazide (HCTZ), triamterene (TA), metformin, cimetidine, ranitidine, quinidine, and nicotine, could potentially result in altered plasma levels of both agents.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'pindolol', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Pindolol has been used with a variety of antihypertensive agents, including hydrochlorothiazide, hydralazine, and guanethidine without unexpected adverse interactions.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'diflunisal', 'N/A', 'major', 'In normal volunteers, concomitant administration of diflunisal and hydrochlorothiazide resulted in significantly increased plasma levels of hydrochlorothiazide. Diflunisal decreased the hyperuricemic effect of hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'moexipril hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'major', 'Other Agents No clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when moexipril hydrochloride was administered concomitantly with hydrochlorothiazide, digoxin, or cimetidine.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'doxazosin', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Doxazosin tablets have been used with the following drugs or drug classes: 1) analgesic/anti-inflammatory (e.g., acetaminophen, aspirin, codeine and codeine combinations, ibuprofen, indomethacin); 2) antibiotics (e.g., erythromycin, trimethoprim and sulfamethoxazole, amoxicillin); 3) antihistamines (e.g., chlorpheniramine); 4) cardiovascular agents (e.g., atenolol, hydrochlorothiazide, propranolol); 5) corticosteroids; 6) gastrointestinal agents (e.g., antacids); 7) hypoglycemics and endocrine drugs; 8) sedatives and tranquilizers (e.g., diazepam); 9) cold and flu remedies.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'fluconazole, sodium chloride', 'N/A', 'contraindicated', 'These are described in greater detail below: Oral hypoglycemics Coumarin-type anticoagulants Phenytoin Cyclosporine Rifampin Theophylline Terfenadine Cisapride Astemizole Rifabutin Voriconazole Tacrolimus Short-acting benzodiazepines Tofacitinib Triazolam Oral Contraceptives Pimozide Quinidine Hydrochlorothiazide Alfentanil Amitriptyline, nortriptyline Amphotericin B Azithromycin Carbamazepine Calcium Channel Blockers Celecoxib Cyclophosphamide Fentanyl Halofantrine HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors Losartan Methadone Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs Prednisone Saquinavir Sirolimus Vinca Alkaloids Vitamin A Zidovudine Oral hypoglycemics Clinically significant hypoglycemia may be precipitated by the use of fluconazole with oral hypoglycemic agents; one fatality has been reported from hypogl', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine besylate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Increased exposure to cyclosporin and tacrolimus Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide (7.3): Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [See Contraindications ( 4 )].', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'dofetilide', 'N/A', 'contraindicated', 'Hydrochlorothiazide (HCTZ) Alone or in Combination with Triamterene (see CONTRAINDICATIONS ) Concomitant use of HCTZ alone or in combination with triamterene is contraindicated.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'olmesartan medoxomil-hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Lithium: Risk of lithium toxicity (7.2) Non-Steroidal Anti-Inflammatory Drugs (NSAIDs): Reduced diuretic, natriuretic and antihypotensive effects; increased risk of renal toxicity (7.3) Dual inhibition of the renin-angiotensin system: Increased risk of renal impairment, hypotension, and hyperkalemia (7.4) Colesevelam hydrochloride: Consider administering olmesartan at least 4 hours before colesevelam hydrochloride dose (7.5) Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment may be required (7.6) Cholestyramine and colestipol: Reduced absorption of thiazides (7.6) 7.1 Agents Increasing Serum Potassium Coadministration of olmesartan medoxomil and hydrochlorothiazide tablets with other drugs that raise serum potassium levels may result in hyperkalemia. 7.2 Lithium Increases in serum l', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'losartan pot/hctz', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Monitor lithium levels in patients receiving losartan potassium and hydrochlorothiazide and lithium. Hydrochlorothiazide The administration of a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory agent including a selective COX-2 inhibitor can reduce the diuretic, natriuretic, and antihypertensive effects of loop, potassium-sparing and thiazide diuretics. Therefore, when losartan potassium and hydrochlorothiazide and non-steroidal anti-inflammatory agents including selective COX-2 inhibitors are used concomitantly, observe closely to determine if the desired effect of the diuretic is obtained.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'fosinopirl sodium', 'N/A', 'minor', 'In separate single or multiple dose pharmacokinetic interaction studies with chlorthalidone, nifedipine, propranolol, hydrochlorothiazide, cimetidine, metoclopramide, propantheline, digoxin, and warfarin, the bioavailability of fosinoprilat was not altered by coadministration of fosinopril with any one of these drugs.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'lithium carbonate', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Reduce lithium dosage based on serum lithium concentration and clinical response [see Dosage and Administration (2.6), Warning and Precautions (5.3)] Examples: hydrochlorothiazide, chlorothiazide, furosemide Non-Steroidal Anti-inflammatory Drugs (NSAID) Clinical Impact: NSAID decrease renal blood flow, resulting in decreased renal clearance and increased serum lithium concentrations.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'In general, avoid combined use of RAS inhibitors, closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes. Avoid use of aliskiren with lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with renal impairment (GFR < 60 ml/min).', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'olmesartan medoxomil and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS • Lithium: Risk of lithium toxicity (7.2) • Non-Steroidal Anti-Inflammatory Drugs (NSAIDs): Reduced diuretic, natriuretic and antihypotensive effects; increased risk of renal toxicity (7.3) • Dual inhibition of the renin-angiotensin system: Increased risk of renal impairment, hypotension, and hyperkalemia (7.4) • Colesevelam hydrochloride: Consider administering olmesartan at least 4 hours before colesevelam hydrochloride dose (7.5) • Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment may be required (7.6) • Cholestyramine and colestipol: Reduced absorption of thiazides (7.6) 7.1 Agents Increasing Serum Potassium Coadministration of olmesartan medoxomil and hydrochlorothiazide tablets with other drugs that raise serum potassium levels may result in hyperkalemia. 7.2 Lithium Increase', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'milrinone lactate in dextrose', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions No untoward clinical manifestations have been observed in limited experience with patients in whom Milrinone was used concurrently with the following drugs: digitalis glycosides; lidocaine, quinidine; hydralazine, prazosin; isosorbide dinitrate, nitroglycerin; chlorthalidone, furosemide, hydrochlorothiazide, spironolactone; captopril; heparin, warfarin, diazepam, insulin; and potassium supplements.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'metoprolol tartrate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide: Hypokalemia can sensitize or exaggerate the response of the heart to the toxic effects of digitalis (e.g., increased ventricular irritability). There have been rare reports in the literature of hemolytic anemia occurring with the concomitant use of hydrochlorothiazide and methyldopa. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins: Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'fosinopril', 'N/A', 'minor', 'In separate single or multiple dose pharmacokinetic interaction studies with chlorthalidone, nifedipine, propranolol, hydrochlorothiazide, cimetidine, metoclopramide, propantheline, digoxin, and warfarin, the bioavailability of fosinoprilat was not altered by coadministration of fosinopril with any one of these drugs.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'telmisartan and amlodipine', 'N/A', 'major', 'Other Drugs: Co-administration of telmisartan did not result in a clinically significant interaction with acetaminophen, amlodipine, glyburide, simvastatin, hydrochlorothiazide, warfarin, or ibuprofen.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'amantadine', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Coadministration of triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide capsules resulted in a higher plasma amantadine concentration in a 61-year-old man receiving amantadine (hydrochloride capsules) 100 mg t.i.d. It is not known which of the components of triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide capsules contributed to the observation or if related drugs produce a similar response.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'captopril and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Gold: Nitritoid reactions (symptoms include facial flushing, nausea, vomiting and hypotension) have been reported rarely in patients on therapy with injectable gold (sodium aurothiomalate) and concomitant ACE inhibitor therapy including captopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets. If a diuretic is also used, it may increase the risk of lithium toxicity (see PRECAUTIONS: Drug Interactions: Hydrochlorothiazide: Lithium ). Hydrochlorothiazide: When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, Barbiturates, or Narcotics: potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'spironolactone and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Pressor Amines (e.g., norepinephrine) Both spironolactone and hydrochlorothiazide reduce the vascular responsiveness to norepinephrine. Therefore, caution should be exercised in the management of patients subjected to regional or general anesthesia while they are being treated with spironolactone and hydrochlorothiazide. Therefore, when spironolactone and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and NSAIDs are used concomitantly, the patient should be observed closely to determine if the desired effect of the diuretic is obtained.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'milrinone lactate in 5% dextrose', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions No untoward clinical manifestations have been observed in limited experience with patients in whom milrinone was used concurrently with the following drugs: digitalis glycosides; lidocaine, quinidine; hydralazine, prazosin; isosorbide dinitrate, nitroglycerin; chlorthalidone, furosemide, hydrochlorothiazide, spironolactone; captopril; heparin, warfarin, diazepam, insulin; and potassium supplements.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'olmesartan medoxomil / amlodipine besylate / hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide ( 7.3): Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. 3 Drug Interactions with Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Antidiabetic Drugs (oral agents and insulin): Dosage adjustment of the antidiabetic drug may be required. Cholestyramine and Colestipol Resins: Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'valsartan/htcz', 'N/A', 'major', 'Valsartan-Hydrochlorothiazide: Lithium: Increases in serum lithium concentrations and lithium toxicity have been reported during concomitant administration of lithium with angiotensin II receptor antagonists or thiazides. Valsartan: No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was coadministered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'amiloride hydrochloride and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Therefore, when amiloride and hydrochlorothiazide plus non-steroidal anti-inflammatory agents are used concomitantly, the patient should be observed closely to determine if the desired effect of the diuretic is obtained. Hydrochlorothiazide When given concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics. Cholestyramine and Colestipol Resins Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'febuxostat tablets 40 mg', 'N/A', 'major', '7.3 In Vivo Drug Interaction Studies Based on drug interaction studies in healthy patients, febuxostat does not have clinically significant interactions with colchicine, naproxen, indomethacin, hydrochlorothiazide, warfarin or desipramine [see Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)].', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'dapagliflozin', 'N/A', 'minor', 'No dosing adjustments required for the following: Oral Antidiabetic Agents Metformin (1000 mg) 20 mg ↔ ↔ Pioglitazone (45 mg) 50 mg ↔ ↔ Sitagliptin (100 mg) 20 mg ↔ ↔ Glimepiride (4 mg) 20 mg ↔ ↔ Voglibose (0.2 mg three times daily) 10 mg ↔ ↔ Other Medications Hydrochlorothiazide (25 mg) 50 mg ↔ ↔ Bumetanide (1 mg) 10 mg once dailyfor 7 days ↔ ↔ Valsartan (320 mg) 20 mg ↓12%[↓3%, ↓20%] ↔ Simvastatin (40 mg) 20 mg ↔ ↔ Anti-infective Agent Rifampin (600 mg once daily for 6 days) 10 mg ↓7%[↓22%, ↑11%] ↓22%[↓27%, ↓17%] Nonsteroidal Anti-inflammatory Agent Mefenamic Acid (loading dose of 500 mg followed by 14 doses of 250 mg every 6 hours) 10 mg ↑13%[↑3%, ↑24%] ↑51%[↑44%, ↑58%] ↔ = no change (geometric mean ratio of test: reference within 0.80 to 1.25); ↓ or ↑ = parameter was lower or higher, r', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No drug interaction studies have been conducted with amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide and other drugs, although studies have been conducted with the individual components. A pharmacokinetic drug-drug interaction study has been conducted to address the potential for pharmacokinetic interaction between the triple combination, amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide, and the corresponding 3 double combinations. Valsartan-Hydrochlorothiazide Lithium Increases in serum lithium concentrations and lithium toxicity have been reported during concomitant administration of lithium with angiotensin II receptor antagonists or thiazides.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'sotalol hydrochloride tables af', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Other No pharmacokinetic interactions were observed with hydrochlorothiazide or warfarin.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'quinapril hydrochloride/hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Drug Interactions Agents Increasing Serum Potassium Coadministration of quinapril and hydrochlorothiazide with other drugs that raise serum potassium levels may result in hyperkalemia. Because renal clearance of lithium is reduced by thiazides, the risk of lithium toxicity is presumably raised further when, as in therapy with quinapril and hydrochlorothiazide, a thiazide diuretic is coadministered with the ACE inhibitor. Quinapril and hydrochlorothiazide and lithium should be coadministered with caution, and frequent monitoring of serum lithium levels is recommended.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'amlodipine,valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No drug interaction studies have been conducted with amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other drugs, although studies have been conducted with the individual components. A pharmacokinetic drug-drug interaction study has been conducted to address the potential for pharmacokinetic interaction between the triple combination, amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide tablets, and the corresponding 3 double combinations. Valsartan – Hydrochlorothiazide Lithium: Increases in serum lithium concentrations and lithium toxicity have been reported during concomitant administration of lithium with angiotensin II receptor antagonists or thiazides.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'amlodipine besylate valsartan hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No drug interaction studies have been conducted with amlodipine/valsartan/hydrochlorothiazide and other drugs, although studies have been conducted with the individual components. A pharmacokinetic drug-drug interaction study has been conducted to address the potential for pharmacokinetic interaction between the triple combination, amlodipine/valsartan/hydrochlorothiazide, and the corresponding 3 double combinations. Valsartan – Hydrochlorothiazide Lithium: Increases in serum lithium concentrations and lithium toxicity have been reported during concomitant administration of lithium with angiotensin II receptor antagonists or thiazides.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'phentermine and topiramate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Concomitant administration of hydrochlorothiazide alone with topiramate alone has been shown to increase the C max and AUC of topiramate by 27% and 29%, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide (7.3): Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine, and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not coadminister aliskiren with olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine, and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [see Contraindications (4)].', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'tolterodine tartrate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Diuretics Coadministration of tolterodine immediate release up to 8 mg (4 mg bid) for up to 12 weeks with diuretic agents, such as indapamide, hydrochlorothiazide, triamterene, bendroflumethiazide, chlorothiazide, methylchlorothiazide, or furosemide, did not cause any adverse electrocardiographic (ECG) effects.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'phentermine and topiramate extended-release', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Concomitant administration of hydrochlorothiazide alone with topiramate alone has been shown to increase the Cmax and AUC of topiramate by 27% and 29%, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'topiramate spinkle', 'N/A', 'minor', '7.5 Hydrochlorothiazide (HCTZ) Topiramate Cmax and AUC increased when HCTZ was added to topiramate.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'fluconazole in sodium chloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide In a pharmacokinetic interaction study, coadministration of multiple-dose hydrochlorothiazide to healthy volunteers receiving fluconazole increased plasma concentrations of fluconazole by 40%.', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablet 20/5/12.5 mg', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Increased exposure to cyclosporin and tacrolimus Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide ( 7.3): Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on Olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with Olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [See Contraindications ( 4)].', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'olmesartan medoxomil and amlodipine besylate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', '•Increased exposure to cyclosporin and tacrolimus •Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide (7.3): •Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine, and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine, and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [See Contraindications (4)].', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'olmesartan medoxomil amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', '• Increased exposure to cyclosporin and tacrolimus • Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide (7.3): • Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [See Contraindications (4 )].', 'DailyMed'),
(14001, 'sucroferric oxyhydroxide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Table 1 Oral drugs that can be administered concomitantly with Velphoro Calcitriol Ciprofloxacin Digoxin Enalapril Furosemide HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide Losartan Metoprolol Nifedipine Omeprazole Quinidine Warfarin Oral drugs that are to be separated from Velphoro Dosing Recommendations Doxycycline Acetylsalicylic acid Cephalexin Take at least 1 hour before Velphoro. Levothyroxine Take at least 4 hours before Velphoro Velphoro can be administered concomitantly with oral calcitriol, ciprofloxacin, digoxin, enalapril, furosemide, HMG‑CoA reductase inhibitors, hydrochlorothiazide, losartan, metoprolol, nifedipine, omeprazole, quinidine and warfarin.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'sotalol hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Other No pharmacokinetic interactions were observed with hydrochlorothiazide or warfarin.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'bisoprolol fumarate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Drug interactions Bisoprolol and hydrochlorothiazide may potentiate the action of other antihypertensive agents used concomitantly. Bisoprolol and hydrochlorothiazide should not be combined with other beta-blocking agents. In patients receiving concurrent therapy with clonidine, if therapy is to be discontinued, it is suggested that bisoprolol and hydrochlorothiazide be discontinued for several days before the withdrawal of clonidine.Bisoprolol and hydrochlorothiazide should be used with caution when myocardial depressants or inhibitors of AV conduction, such as certain calcium antagonists [particularly of the phenylalkylamine (verapamil) and benzothiazepine (diltiazem) classes], or antiarrhythmic agents, such as disopyramide, are used concurrently.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'sotalol', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Other No pharmacokinetic interactions were observed with hydrochlorothiazide or warfarin.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions When given concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics.Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcoticsPotentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur.Antidiabetic drugs - (oral agents and insulin)Dosage adjustment of the antidiabetic drug may be required.Other antihypertensive drugsAdditive effect or potentiation.Cholestryamine and colestipol resinsAbsorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins. Single doses of either cholestyramine or colestipol resins bind the hydrochlorothiazide and reduce its absorption from the gastrointestinal tract by up to 85 and 43 percent, respectively.Corticosteroids, ACTHIntensified electrolyte depletion, particularly hypokalemia.Pressor amines (e.g., norepinephrine)Possible decreased r', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'No meaningful clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when lisinopril was used concomitantly with propranolol, digoxin, or hydrochlorothiazide. It is recommended that serum lithium levels be monitored frequently if lisinopril is administered concomitantly with lithium.Hydrochlorothiazide: When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics.Alcohol, Barbiturates, Or Narcotics— potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur.Antidiabetic Drugs (Oral Agents And Insulin) — dosage adjustment of the antidiabetic drug may be required.Other Antihypertensive Drugs — additive effect or potentiation.Cholestyramine And Colestipol Resins — Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins. Single doses of ei', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Acute renal failure has been reported in a few patients receiving indomethacin and formulations containing triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide. Caution is therefore advised when administering nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory agents with triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'doxazosin mesylate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Doxazosin mesylate tablets have been used with the following drugs or drug classes: 1) analgesic/anti-inflammatory (e.g., acetaminophen, aspirin, codeine and codeine combinations, ibuprofen, indomethacin); 2) antibiotics (e.g., erythromycin, trimethoprim and sulfamethoxazole, amoxicillin); 3) antihistamines (e.g., chlorpheniramine); 4) cardiovascular agents (e.g., atenolol, hydrochlorothiazide, propranolol); 5) corticosteroids; 6) gastrointestinal agents (e.g., antacids); 7) hypoglycemics and endocrine drugs; 8) sedatives and tranquilizers (e.g., diazepam); 9) cold and flu remedies.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'benazepril hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'major', 'Other No clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when benazepril hydrochloride tablets were administered concomitantly with hydrochlorothiazide, chlorthalidone, furosemide, digoxin, propranolol, atenolol, naproxen, or cimetidine.', 'DailyMed');
INSERT INTO drug_interactions (med_id, interaction_drug_name, interaction_dailymed_id, severity, description, source) VALUES
(2868, 'fosinopril sodium and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions Potassium supplements and potassium-sparing diuretics: As noted above ("Derangements of Serum Electrolytes"), the net effect of fosinopril sodium and hydrochlorothiazide may be to elevate a patient''s serum potassium, to reduce it, or to leave it unchanged. Because renal clearance of lithium is reduced by thiazides, the risk of lithium toxicity is presumably raised further when, as in therapy with fosinopril sodium and hydrochlorothiazide tablets, a thiazide diuretic is coadministered with the ACE inhibitor. Other ACE inhibitors have had less than additive effects with betaadrenergic blockers, presumably because drugs of both classes lower blood pressure by inhibiting parts of the renin-angiotensin system.Interaction studies with warfarin have failed to identify any clinic', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'quinapril', 'N/A', 'minor', 'No pharmacokinetic interaction was observed when single doses of quinapril hydrochloride andhydrochlorothiazide were administered concomitantly.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'lisinopril', 'N/A', 'major', 'No clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when lisinopril was used concomitantly with propranolol or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'terazosin hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Terazosin has been used concomitantly in at least 50 patients on the following drugs or drug classes: 1) analgesic/anti-inflammatory (e.g., acetaminophen, aspirin, codeine, ibuprofen, indomethacin); 2) antibiotics (e.g., erythromycin, trimethoprim and sulfamethoxazole); 3) anticholinergic/sympathomimetics (e.g., phenylephrine hydrochloride, phenylpropanolamine hydrochloride, pseudoephedrine hydrochloride); 4) antigout (e.g., allopurinol); 5) antihistamines (e.g., chlorpheniramine); 6) cardiovascular agents (e.g., atenolol, hydrochlorothiazide, methyclothiazide, propranolol); 7) corticosteroids; 8) gastrointestinal agents (e.g., antacids); 9) hypoglycemics; 10) sedatives and tranquilizers (e.g., diazepam).', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'drug_class', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions When given concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'irbesartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '[See Clinical Pharmacology (12.3).] Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, Barbiturates, or Narcotics: potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and Colestipol Resins: absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins. Single doses of either cholestyramine or colestipol resins bind the hydrochlorothiazide and reduce its absorption from the gastrointestinal tract by up to 85% and 43%, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'carvedilol phosphate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide A single oral dose of carvedilol 25 mg did not alter the pharmacokinetics of a single oral dose of hydrochlorothiazide 25 mg in 12 patients with hypertension. Likewise, hydrochlorothiazide had no effect on the pharmacokinetics of carvedilol.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'colestipol hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'major', 'The absorption of tetracycline, furosemide, penicillin G, hydrochlorothiazide, and gemfibrozil was significantly decreased when given simultaneously with colestipol hydrochloride; these drugs were not tested to determine the effect of administration one hour before colestipol hydrochloride.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'aliskiren hemifumarate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No drug interaction studies have been conducted with Tekturna HCT and other drugs, although studies with the individual aliskiren and hydrochlorothiazide components are described below. Drugs with no clinically significant effects: Coadministration of lovastatin, atenolol, warfarin, furosemide, digoxin, celecoxib, hydrochlorothiazide, ramipril, valsartan, metformin and amlodipine did not result in clinically significant increases in aliskiren exposure. Drugs with no clinically significant effects: Coadministration of aliskiren did not significantly affect the pharmacokinetics of lovastatin, digoxin, valsartan, amlodipine, metformin, celecoxib, atenolol, atorvastatin, ramipril or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'etodolac', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Diuretics Etodolac has no apparent pharmacokinetic interaction when administered with furosemide or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'amantadine hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Coadministration of Dyazide (triamterene/hydrochlorothiazide) resulted in a higher plasma amantadine concentration in a 61-year-old man receiving amantadine 100 mg TID for Parkinson''s disease.1 It is not known which of the components of Dyazide contributed to the observation or if related drugs produce a similar response.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'enalapril maleate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics – potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins – Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins. Single doses of either cholestyramine or colestipol resins bind the hydrochlorothiazide and reduce its absorption from the gastrointestinal tract by up to 85 and 43 percent, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'ketoprofen', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide, given concomitantly with ketoprofen, produces a reduction in urinary potassium and chloride excretion compared to hydrochlorothiazide alone.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'febuxostat', 'N/A', 'major', '7.3 In Vivo Drug Interaction Studies Based on drug interaction studies in healthy subjects, ULORIC does not have clinically significant interactions with colchicine, naproxen, indomethacin, hydrochlorothiazide, warfarin or desipramine [see Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)].', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'pramipexole dihydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Other drugs eliminated via renal secretion: Population pharmacokinetic analysis suggests that coadministration of drugs that are secreted by the cationic transport system (e.g., cimetidine, ranitidine, diltiazem, triamterene, verapamil, quinidine, and quinine) decreases the oral clearance of pramipexole by about 20%, while those secreted by the anionic transport system (e.g., cephalosporins, penicillins, indomethacin, hydrochlorothiazide, and chlorpropamide) are likely to have little effect on the oral clearance of pramipexole.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'losartan potassium and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'There is no pharmacokinetic interaction between losartan and hydrochlorothiazide. Hydrochlorothiazide After oral administration of hydrochlorothiazide, diuresis begins within 2 hours, peaks in about 4 hours and lasts about 6 to 12 hours. Hydrochlorothiazide is not metabolized but is eliminated rapidly by the kidney.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'topiramate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide (HCTZ): A drug-drug interaction study conducted in healthy volunteers evaluated the steady-state pharmacokinetics of HCTZ (25 mg q24h) and topiramate (96 mg q12h) when administered alone and concomitantly.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'valsartan', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when Diovan (valsartan) was coadministered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'lisinopril, arginine', 'N/A', 'major', 'No clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when Lisinopril Tablets were used concomitantly with propranolol or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'losartan potassium', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions No significant drug-drug pharmacokinetic interactions have been found in interaction studies with hydrochlorothiazide, digoxin, warfarin, cimetidine and phenobarbital.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'milrinone lactate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions No untoward clinical manifestations have been observed in limited experience with patients in whom milrinone was used concurrently with the following drugs: digitalis glycosides; lidocaine, quinidine; hydralazine, prazosin; isosorbide dinitrate, nitroglycerin; chlorthalidone, furosemide, hydrochlorothiazide, spironolactone; captopril; heparin, warfarin, diazepam, insulin; and potassium supplements.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'irbesartan', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions No significant drug-drug pharmacokinetic (or pharmacodynamic) interactions have been found in interaction studies with hydrochlorothiazide, digoxin, warfarin, and nifedipine. In separate studies of patients receiving maintenance doses of warfarin, hydrochlorothiazide, or digoxin, irbesartan administration for 7 days had no effect on the pharmacodynamics of warfarin (prothrombin time) or pharmacokinetics of digoxin. The pharmacokinetics of irbesartan were not affected by coadministration of nifedipine or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'amlodipine valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'Valsartan No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was co-administered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin. Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics: Potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins: Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'eprosartan mesylate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Or 800 mg q.d.) doses have been safely used concomitantly with a thiazide diuretic (hydrochlorothiazide). Hydrochlorothiazide: When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics – potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins – Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Valsartan: No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was coadministered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin. Hydrochlorothiazide: When administered concurrently, the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, Barbiturates, or N arcotics - Potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and Colestipol R esins - Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'amlodipine besylate and valsartan', 'N/A', 'major', 'Studies with Valsartan No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was co-administered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'acebutolol hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'major', 'No significant interactions with digoxin, hydrochlorothiazide, hydralazine, sulfinpyrazone, oral contraceptives, tolbutamide, or warfarin have been observed.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'candesartan cilexetil and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions Candesartan Cilexetil No significant drug interactions have been reported in studies of candesartan cilexetil given with other drugs such as glyburide, nifedipine, digoxin, warfarin, hydrochlorothiazide, and oral contraceptives in healthy volunteers. Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics − Potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins − Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'telmisartan', 'N/A', 'major', 'Other Drugs: Co-administration of telmisartan did not result in a clinically significant interaction with acetaminophen, amlodipine, glyburide, simvastatin, hydrochlorothiazide, warfarin, or ibuprofen.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'telmisartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'Because lithium should not be used with diuretics, the use of lithium with telmisartan and hydrochlorothiazide is not recommended. Other Drugs: Co-administration of telmisartan did not result in a clinically significant interaction with acetaminophen, amlodipine, glibenclamide, simvastatin, hydrochlorothiazide or ibuprofen. Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently, the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics: Potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'benazepril hydrochloride and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Cholestyramine and colestipol resins: Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins. Single doses of either cholestyramine or colestipol resins bind the hydrochlorothiazide and reduce its absorption from the gastrointestinal tract by up to 85% and 43%, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'betaxolol', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions The following drugs have been coadministered with betaxolol and have not altered its pharmacokinetics: cimetidine, nifedipine, chlorthalidone, and hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'fluconazole', 'N/A', 'contraindicated', 'These are described in greater detail below: Oral hypoglycemics Coumarin-type anticoagulants Phenytoin Cyclosporine Rifampin Theophylline Terfenadine Cisapride Astemizole Rifabutin Voriconazole Tacrolimus Short-acting benzodiazepines Triazolam Oral Contraceptives Pimozide Hydrochlorothiazide Alfentanil Amitriptyline, nortriptyline Amphotericin B Azithromycin Carbamazepine Calcium Channel Blockers Celecoxib Cyclophosphamide Fentanyl Halofantrine HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors Losartan Methadone Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs Prednisone Saquinavir Sirolimus Vinca Alkaloids Vitamin A Zidovudine Oral hypoglycemics: Clinically significant hypoglycemia may be precipitated by the use of fluconazole with oral hypoglycemic agents; one fatality has been reported from hypoglycemia in association', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'fosinopril sodium', 'N/A', 'minor', 'In separate single or multiple dose pharmacokinetic interaction studies with chlorthalidone, nifedipine, propranolol, hydrochlorothiazide, cimetidine, metoclopramide, propantheline, digoxin, and warfarin, the bioavailability of fosinoprilat was not altered by coadministration of fosinopril with any one of these drugs.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'candesartan cilexetil', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No significant drug interactions have been reported in studies of candesartan cilexetil given with other drugs such as glyburide, nifedipine, digoxin, warfarin, hydrochlorothiazide, and oral contraceptives in healthy volunteers, or given with enalapril to patients with heart failure (NYHA class II and III).', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'losartan potatssium', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions No significant drug-drug pharmacokinetic interactions have been found in interaction studies with hydrochlorothiazide, digoxin, warfarin, cimetidine and phenobarbital.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'terazosin', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Terazosin has been used concomitantly in at least 50 patients on the following drugs or drug classes: 1) analgesic/anti-inflammatory (e.g., acetaminophen, aspirin, codeine, ibuprofen, indomethacin); 2) antibiotics (e.g., erythromycin, trimethoprim and sulfamethoxazole); 3) anticholinergic/sympathomimetics (e.g., phenylephrine hydrochloride, phenylpropanolamine hydrochloride, pseudoephedrine hydrochloride); 4) antigout (e.g., allopurinol); 5) antihistamines (e.g., chlorpheniramine); 6) cardiovascular agents (e.g., atenolol, hydrochlorothiazide, methyclothiazide, propranolol); 7) corticosteroids; 8) gastrointestinal agents (e.g., antacids); 9) hypoglycemics; 10) sedatives and tranquilizers (e.g., diazepam).', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'carbamazepine', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Concomitant medication with carbamazepine and some diuretics (hydrochlorothiazide, furosemide) may lead to symptomatic hyponatremia.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'quinapril hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'No pharmacokinetic interaction was observed when single doses of quinapril hydrochloride and hydrochlorothiazide were administered concomitantly.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'isradipine', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Nitroglycerin: A study in normal healthy volunteers has shown that concomitant administration of isradipine and hydrochlorothiazide does not result in altered pharmacokinetics of either drug. In a study in hypertensive patients, addition of isradipine to existing hydrochlorothiazide therapy did not result in any unexpected adverse effects, and isradipine had an additional antihypertensive effect. Hydrochlorothiazide: In a single dose study in normal volunteers, co-administration of propranolol had a small effect on the rate but no effect on the extent of isradipine bioavailability.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'amlodipine and valsartan', 'N/A', 'major', 'Studies with Valsartan No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was co-administered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'quinapril hydrochloride and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Drug Interactions Agents Increasing Serum Potassium: Coadministration of quinapril HCl and hydrochlorothiazide tablets with other drugs that raise serum potassium levels may result in hyperkalemia. Because renal clearance of lithium is reduced by thiazides, the risk of lithium toxicity is presumably raised further when, as in therapy with quinapril HCl and hydrochlorothiazide tablets, a thiazide diuretic is coadministered with the ACE inhibitor. Quinapril HCl and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and lithium should be coadministered with caution, and frequent monitoring of serum lithium levels is recommended.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'memantine hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', '7.4 Drugs Eliminated via Renal Mechanisms Because memantine is eliminated in part by tubular secretion, coadministration of drugs that use the same renal cationic system, including hydrochlorothiazide (HCTZ), triamterene (TA), metformin, cimetidine, ranitidine, quinidine, and nicotine, could potentially result in altered plasma levels of both agents.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'pindolol', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Pindolol has been used with a variety of antihypertensive agents, including hydrochlorothiazide, hydralazine, and guanethidine without unexpected adverse interactions.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'diflunisal', 'N/A', 'major', 'In normal volunteers, concomitant administration of diflunisal and hydrochlorothiazide resulted in significantly increased plasma levels of hydrochlorothiazide. Diflunisal decreased the hyperuricemic effect of hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'moexipril hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'major', 'Other Agents No clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when moexipril hydrochloride was administered concomitantly with hydrochlorothiazide, digoxin, or cimetidine.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'doxazosin', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Doxazosin tablets have been used with the following drugs or drug classes: 1) analgesic/anti-inflammatory (e.g., acetaminophen, aspirin, codeine and codeine combinations, ibuprofen, indomethacin); 2) antibiotics (e.g., erythromycin, trimethoprim and sulfamethoxazole, amoxicillin); 3) antihistamines (e.g., chlorpheniramine); 4) cardiovascular agents (e.g., atenolol, hydrochlorothiazide, propranolol); 5) corticosteroids; 6) gastrointestinal agents (e.g., antacids); 7) hypoglycemics and endocrine drugs; 8) sedatives and tranquilizers (e.g., diazepam); 9) cold and flu remedies.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'fluconazole, sodium chloride', 'N/A', 'contraindicated', 'These are described in greater detail below: Oral hypoglycemics Coumarin-type anticoagulants Phenytoin Cyclosporine Rifampin Theophylline Terfenadine Cisapride Astemizole Rifabutin Voriconazole Tacrolimus Short-acting benzodiazepines Tofacitinib Triazolam Oral Contraceptives Pimozide Quinidine Hydrochlorothiazide Alfentanil Amitriptyline, nortriptyline Amphotericin B Azithromycin Carbamazepine Calcium Channel Blockers Celecoxib Cyclophosphamide Fentanyl Halofantrine HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors Losartan Methadone Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs Prednisone Saquinavir Sirolimus Vinca Alkaloids Vitamin A Zidovudine Oral hypoglycemics Clinically significant hypoglycemia may be precipitated by the use of fluconazole with oral hypoglycemic agents; one fatality has been reported from hypogl', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine besylate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Increased exposure to cyclosporin and tacrolimus Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide (7.3): Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [See Contraindications ( 4 )].', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'dofetilide', 'N/A', 'contraindicated', 'Hydrochlorothiazide (HCTZ) Alone or in Combination with Triamterene (see CONTRAINDICATIONS ) Concomitant use of HCTZ alone or in combination with triamterene is contraindicated.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'olmesartan medoxomil-hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Lithium: Risk of lithium toxicity (7.2) Non-Steroidal Anti-Inflammatory Drugs (NSAIDs): Reduced diuretic, natriuretic and antihypotensive effects; increased risk of renal toxicity (7.3) Dual inhibition of the renin-angiotensin system: Increased risk of renal impairment, hypotension, and hyperkalemia (7.4) Colesevelam hydrochloride: Consider administering olmesartan at least 4 hours before colesevelam hydrochloride dose (7.5) Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment may be required (7.6) Cholestyramine and colestipol: Reduced absorption of thiazides (7.6) 7.1 Agents Increasing Serum Potassium Coadministration of olmesartan medoxomil and hydrochlorothiazide tablets with other drugs that raise serum potassium levels may result in hyperkalemia. 7.2 Lithium Increases in serum l', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'losartan pot/hctz', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Monitor lithium levels in patients receiving losartan potassium and hydrochlorothiazide and lithium. Hydrochlorothiazide The administration of a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory agent including a selective COX-2 inhibitor can reduce the diuretic, natriuretic, and antihypertensive effects of loop, potassium-sparing and thiazide diuretics. Therefore, when losartan potassium and hydrochlorothiazide and non-steroidal anti-inflammatory agents including selective COX-2 inhibitors are used concomitantly, observe closely to determine if the desired effect of the diuretic is obtained.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'fosinopirl sodium', 'N/A', 'minor', 'In separate single or multiple dose pharmacokinetic interaction studies with chlorthalidone, nifedipine, propranolol, hydrochlorothiazide, cimetidine, metoclopramide, propantheline, digoxin, and warfarin, the bioavailability of fosinoprilat was not altered by coadministration of fosinopril with any one of these drugs.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'lithium carbonate', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Reduce lithium dosage based on serum lithium concentration and clinical response [see Dosage and Administration (2.6), Warning and Precautions (5.3)] Examples: hydrochlorothiazide, chlorothiazide, furosemide Non-Steroidal Anti-inflammatory Drugs (NSAID) Clinical Impact: NSAID decrease renal blood flow, resulting in decreased renal clearance and increased serum lithium concentrations.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'In general, avoid combined use of RAS inhibitors, closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes. Avoid use of aliskiren with lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with renal impairment (GFR < 60 ml/min).', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'olmesartan medoxomil and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS • Lithium: Risk of lithium toxicity (7.2) • Non-Steroidal Anti-Inflammatory Drugs (NSAIDs): Reduced diuretic, natriuretic and antihypotensive effects; increased risk of renal toxicity (7.3) • Dual inhibition of the renin-angiotensin system: Increased risk of renal impairment, hypotension, and hyperkalemia (7.4) • Colesevelam hydrochloride: Consider administering olmesartan at least 4 hours before colesevelam hydrochloride dose (7.5) • Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment may be required (7.6) • Cholestyramine and colestipol: Reduced absorption of thiazides (7.6) 7.1 Agents Increasing Serum Potassium Coadministration of olmesartan medoxomil and hydrochlorothiazide tablets with other drugs that raise serum potassium levels may result in hyperkalemia. 7.2 Lithium Increase', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'milrinone lactate in dextrose', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions No untoward clinical manifestations have been observed in limited experience with patients in whom Milrinone was used concurrently with the following drugs: digitalis glycosides; lidocaine, quinidine; hydralazine, prazosin; isosorbide dinitrate, nitroglycerin; chlorthalidone, furosemide, hydrochlorothiazide, spironolactone; captopril; heparin, warfarin, diazepam, insulin; and potassium supplements.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'metoprolol tartrate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide: Hypokalemia can sensitize or exaggerate the response of the heart to the toxic effects of digitalis (e.g., increased ventricular irritability). There have been rare reports in the literature of hemolytic anemia occurring with the concomitant use of hydrochlorothiazide and methyldopa. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins: Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'fosinopril', 'N/A', 'minor', 'In separate single or multiple dose pharmacokinetic interaction studies with chlorthalidone, nifedipine, propranolol, hydrochlorothiazide, cimetidine, metoclopramide, propantheline, digoxin, and warfarin, the bioavailability of fosinoprilat was not altered by coadministration of fosinopril with any one of these drugs.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'telmisartan and amlodipine', 'N/A', 'major', 'Other Drugs: Co-administration of telmisartan did not result in a clinically significant interaction with acetaminophen, amlodipine, glyburide, simvastatin, hydrochlorothiazide, warfarin, or ibuprofen.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'amantadine', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Coadministration of triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide capsules resulted in a higher plasma amantadine concentration in a 61-year-old man receiving amantadine (hydrochloride capsules) 100 mg t.i.d. It is not known which of the components of triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide capsules contributed to the observation or if related drugs produce a similar response.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'captopril and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Gold: Nitritoid reactions (symptoms include facial flushing, nausea, vomiting and hypotension) have been reported rarely in patients on therapy with injectable gold (sodium aurothiomalate) and concomitant ACE inhibitor therapy including captopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets. If a diuretic is also used, it may increase the risk of lithium toxicity (see PRECAUTIONS: Drug Interactions: Hydrochlorothiazide: Lithium ). Hydrochlorothiazide: When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, Barbiturates, or Narcotics: potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'spironolactone and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Pressor Amines (e.g., norepinephrine) Both spironolactone and hydrochlorothiazide reduce the vascular responsiveness to norepinephrine. Therefore, caution should be exercised in the management of patients subjected to regional or general anesthesia while they are being treated with spironolactone and hydrochlorothiazide. Therefore, when spironolactone and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and NSAIDs are used concomitantly, the patient should be observed closely to determine if the desired effect of the diuretic is obtained.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'milrinone lactate in 5% dextrose', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions No untoward clinical manifestations have been observed in limited experience with patients in whom milrinone was used concurrently with the following drugs: digitalis glycosides; lidocaine, quinidine; hydralazine, prazosin; isosorbide dinitrate, nitroglycerin; chlorthalidone, furosemide, hydrochlorothiazide, spironolactone; captopril; heparin, warfarin, diazepam, insulin; and potassium supplements.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'olmesartan medoxomil / amlodipine besylate / hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide ( 7.3): Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. 3 Drug Interactions with Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Antidiabetic Drugs (oral agents and insulin): Dosage adjustment of the antidiabetic drug may be required. Cholestyramine and Colestipol Resins: Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'valsartan/htcz', 'N/A', 'major', 'Valsartan-Hydrochlorothiazide: Lithium: Increases in serum lithium concentrations and lithium toxicity have been reported during concomitant administration of lithium with angiotensin II receptor antagonists or thiazides. Valsartan: No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was coadministered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'amiloride hydrochloride and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Therefore, when amiloride and hydrochlorothiazide plus non-steroidal anti-inflammatory agents are used concomitantly, the patient should be observed closely to determine if the desired effect of the diuretic is obtained. Hydrochlorothiazide When given concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics. Cholestyramine and Colestipol Resins Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'febuxostat tablets 40 mg', 'N/A', 'major', '7.3 In Vivo Drug Interaction Studies Based on drug interaction studies in healthy patients, febuxostat does not have clinically significant interactions with colchicine, naproxen, indomethacin, hydrochlorothiazide, warfarin or desipramine [see Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)].', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'dapagliflozin', 'N/A', 'minor', 'No dosing adjustments required for the following: Oral Antidiabetic Agents Metformin (1000 mg) 20 mg ↔ ↔ Pioglitazone (45 mg) 50 mg ↔ ↔ Sitagliptin (100 mg) 20 mg ↔ ↔ Glimepiride (4 mg) 20 mg ↔ ↔ Voglibose (0.2 mg three times daily) 10 mg ↔ ↔ Other Medications Hydrochlorothiazide (25 mg) 50 mg ↔ ↔ Bumetanide (1 mg) 10 mg once dailyfor 7 days ↔ ↔ Valsartan (320 mg) 20 mg ↓12%[↓3%, ↓20%] ↔ Simvastatin (40 mg) 20 mg ↔ ↔ Anti-infective Agent Rifampin (600 mg once daily for 6 days) 10 mg ↓7%[↓22%, ↑11%] ↓22%[↓27%, ↓17%] Nonsteroidal Anti-inflammatory Agent Mefenamic Acid (loading dose of 500 mg followed by 14 doses of 250 mg every 6 hours) 10 mg ↑13%[↑3%, ↑24%] ↑51%[↑44%, ↑58%] ↔ = no change (geometric mean ratio of test: reference within 0.80 to 1.25); ↓ or ↑ = parameter was lower or higher, r', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No drug interaction studies have been conducted with amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide and other drugs, although studies have been conducted with the individual components. A pharmacokinetic drug-drug interaction study has been conducted to address the potential for pharmacokinetic interaction between the triple combination, amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide, and the corresponding 3 double combinations. Valsartan-Hydrochlorothiazide Lithium Increases in serum lithium concentrations and lithium toxicity have been reported during concomitant administration of lithium with angiotensin II receptor antagonists or thiazides.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'sotalol hydrochloride tables af', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Other No pharmacokinetic interactions were observed with hydrochlorothiazide or warfarin.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'quinapril hydrochloride/hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Drug Interactions Agents Increasing Serum Potassium Coadministration of quinapril and hydrochlorothiazide with other drugs that raise serum potassium levels may result in hyperkalemia. Because renal clearance of lithium is reduced by thiazides, the risk of lithium toxicity is presumably raised further when, as in therapy with quinapril and hydrochlorothiazide, a thiazide diuretic is coadministered with the ACE inhibitor. Quinapril and hydrochlorothiazide and lithium should be coadministered with caution, and frequent monitoring of serum lithium levels is recommended.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'amlodipine,valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No drug interaction studies have been conducted with amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other drugs, although studies have been conducted with the individual components. A pharmacokinetic drug-drug interaction study has been conducted to address the potential for pharmacokinetic interaction between the triple combination, amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide tablets, and the corresponding 3 double combinations. Valsartan – Hydrochlorothiazide Lithium: Increases in serum lithium concentrations and lithium toxicity have been reported during concomitant administration of lithium with angiotensin II receptor antagonists or thiazides.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'amlodipine besylate valsartan hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No drug interaction studies have been conducted with amlodipine/valsartan/hydrochlorothiazide and other drugs, although studies have been conducted with the individual components. A pharmacokinetic drug-drug interaction study has been conducted to address the potential for pharmacokinetic interaction between the triple combination, amlodipine/valsartan/hydrochlorothiazide, and the corresponding 3 double combinations. Valsartan – Hydrochlorothiazide Lithium: Increases in serum lithium concentrations and lithium toxicity have been reported during concomitant administration of lithium with angiotensin II receptor antagonists or thiazides.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'phentermine and topiramate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Concomitant administration of hydrochlorothiazide alone with topiramate alone has been shown to increase the C max and AUC of topiramate by 27% and 29%, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide (7.3): Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine, and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not coadminister aliskiren with olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine, and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [see Contraindications (4)].', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'tolterodine tartrate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Diuretics Coadministration of tolterodine immediate release up to 8 mg (4 mg bid) for up to 12 weeks with diuretic agents, such as indapamide, hydrochlorothiazide, triamterene, bendroflumethiazide, chlorothiazide, methylchlorothiazide, or furosemide, did not cause any adverse electrocardiographic (ECG) effects.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'phentermine and topiramate extended-release', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Concomitant administration of hydrochlorothiazide alone with topiramate alone has been shown to increase the Cmax and AUC of topiramate by 27% and 29%, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'topiramate spinkle', 'N/A', 'minor', '7.5 Hydrochlorothiazide (HCTZ) Topiramate Cmax and AUC increased when HCTZ was added to topiramate.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'fluconazole in sodium chloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide In a pharmacokinetic interaction study, coadministration of multiple-dose hydrochlorothiazide to healthy volunteers receiving fluconazole increased plasma concentrations of fluconazole by 40%.', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablet 20/5/12.5 mg', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Increased exposure to cyclosporin and tacrolimus Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide ( 7.3): Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on Olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with Olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [See Contraindications ( 4)].', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'olmesartan medoxomil and amlodipine besylate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', '•Increased exposure to cyclosporin and tacrolimus •Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide (7.3): •Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine, and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine, and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [See Contraindications (4)].', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'olmesartan medoxomil amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', '• Increased exposure to cyclosporin and tacrolimus • Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide (7.3): • Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [See Contraindications (4 )].', 'DailyMed'),
(2868, 'sucroferric oxyhydroxide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Table 1 Oral drugs that can be administered concomitantly with Velphoro Calcitriol Ciprofloxacin Digoxin Enalapril Furosemide HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide Losartan Metoprolol Nifedipine Omeprazole Quinidine Warfarin Oral drugs that are to be separated from Velphoro Dosing Recommendations Doxycycline Acetylsalicylic acid Cephalexin Take at least 1 hour before Velphoro. Levothyroxine Take at least 4 hours before Velphoro Velphoro can be administered concomitantly with oral calcitriol, ciprofloxacin, digoxin, enalapril, furosemide, HMG‑CoA reductase inhibitors, hydrochlorothiazide, losartan, metoprolol, nifedipine, omeprazole, quinidine and warfarin.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'sotalol hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Other No pharmacokinetic interactions were observed with hydrochlorothiazide or warfarin.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'bisoprolol fumarate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Drug interactions Bisoprolol and hydrochlorothiazide may potentiate the action of other antihypertensive agents used concomitantly. Bisoprolol and hydrochlorothiazide should not be combined with other beta-blocking agents. In patients receiving concurrent therapy with clonidine, if therapy is to be discontinued, it is suggested that bisoprolol and hydrochlorothiazide be discontinued for several days before the withdrawal of clonidine.Bisoprolol and hydrochlorothiazide should be used with caution when myocardial depressants or inhibitors of AV conduction, such as certain calcium antagonists [particularly of the phenylalkylamine (verapamil) and benzothiazepine (diltiazem) classes], or antiarrhythmic agents, such as disopyramide, are used concurrently.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'sotalol', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Other No pharmacokinetic interactions were observed with hydrochlorothiazide or warfarin.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'No meaningful clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when lisinopril was used concomitantly with propranolol, digoxin, or hydrochlorothiazide. It is recommended that serum lithium levels be monitored frequently if lisinopril is administered concomitantly with lithium.Hydrochlorothiazide: When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics.Alcohol, Barbiturates, Or Narcotics— potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur.Antidiabetic Drugs (Oral Agents And Insulin) — dosage adjustment of the antidiabetic drug may be required.Other Antihypertensive Drugs — additive effect or potentiation.Cholestyramine And Colestipol Resins — Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins. Single doses of ei', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Acute renal failure has been reported in a few patients receiving indomethacin and formulations containing triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide. Caution is therefore advised when administering nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory agents with triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'doxazosin mesylate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Doxazosin mesylate tablets have been used with the following drugs or drug classes: 1) analgesic/anti-inflammatory (e.g., acetaminophen, aspirin, codeine and codeine combinations, ibuprofen, indomethacin); 2) antibiotics (e.g., erythromycin, trimethoprim and sulfamethoxazole, amoxicillin); 3) antihistamines (e.g., chlorpheniramine); 4) cardiovascular agents (e.g., atenolol, hydrochlorothiazide, propranolol); 5) corticosteroids; 6) gastrointestinal agents (e.g., antacids); 7) hypoglycemics and endocrine drugs; 8) sedatives and tranquilizers (e.g., diazepam); 9) cold and flu remedies.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'benazepril hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'major', 'Other No clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when benazepril hydrochloride tablets were administered concomitantly with hydrochlorothiazide, chlorthalidone, furosemide, digoxin, propranolol, atenolol, naproxen, or cimetidine.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'fosinopril sodium and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions Potassium supplements and potassium-sparing diuretics: As noted above ("Derangements of Serum Electrolytes"), the net effect of fosinopril sodium and hydrochlorothiazide may be to elevate a patient''s serum potassium, to reduce it, or to leave it unchanged. Because renal clearance of lithium is reduced by thiazides, the risk of lithium toxicity is presumably raised further when, as in therapy with fosinopril sodium and hydrochlorothiazide tablets, a thiazide diuretic is coadministered with the ACE inhibitor. Other ACE inhibitors have had less than additive effects with betaadrenergic blockers, presumably because drugs of both classes lower blood pressure by inhibiting parts of the renin-angiotensin system.Interaction studies with warfarin have failed to identify any clinic', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'quinapril', 'N/A', 'minor', 'No pharmacokinetic interaction was observed when single doses of quinapril hydrochloride andhydrochlorothiazide were administered concomitantly.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'lisinopril', 'N/A', 'major', 'No clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when lisinopril was used concomitantly with propranolol or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'terazosin hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Terazosin has been used concomitantly in at least 50 patients on the following drugs or drug classes: 1) analgesic/anti-inflammatory (e.g., acetaminophen, aspirin, codeine, ibuprofen, indomethacin); 2) antibiotics (e.g., erythromycin, trimethoprim and sulfamethoxazole); 3) anticholinergic/sympathomimetics (e.g., phenylephrine hydrochloride, phenylpropanolamine hydrochloride, pseudoephedrine hydrochloride); 4) antigout (e.g., allopurinol); 5) antihistamines (e.g., chlorpheniramine); 6) cardiovascular agents (e.g., atenolol, hydrochlorothiazide, methyclothiazide, propranolol); 7) corticosteroids; 8) gastrointestinal agents (e.g., antacids); 9) hypoglycemics; 10) sedatives and tranquilizers (e.g., diazepam).', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'drug_class', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions When given concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'irbesartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '[See Clinical Pharmacology (12.3).] Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, Barbiturates, or Narcotics: potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and Colestipol Resins: absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins. Single doses of either cholestyramine or colestipol resins bind the hydrochlorothiazide and reduce its absorption from the gastrointestinal tract by up to 85% and 43%, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'carvedilol phosphate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide A single oral dose of carvedilol 25 mg did not alter the pharmacokinetics of a single oral dose of hydrochlorothiazide 25 mg in 12 patients with hypertension. Likewise, hydrochlorothiazide had no effect on the pharmacokinetics of carvedilol.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'colestipol hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'major', 'The absorption of tetracycline, furosemide, penicillin G, hydrochlorothiazide, and gemfibrozil was significantly decreased when given simultaneously with colestipol hydrochloride; these drugs were not tested to determine the effect of administration one hour before colestipol hydrochloride.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'aliskiren hemifumarate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No drug interaction studies have been conducted with Tekturna HCT and other drugs, although studies with the individual aliskiren and hydrochlorothiazide components are described below. Drugs with no clinically significant effects: Coadministration of lovastatin, atenolol, warfarin, furosemide, digoxin, celecoxib, hydrochlorothiazide, ramipril, valsartan, metformin and amlodipine did not result in clinically significant increases in aliskiren exposure. Drugs with no clinically significant effects: Coadministration of aliskiren did not significantly affect the pharmacokinetics of lovastatin, digoxin, valsartan, amlodipine, metformin, celecoxib, atenolol, atorvastatin, ramipril or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed');
INSERT INTO drug_interactions (med_id, interaction_drug_name, interaction_dailymed_id, severity, description, source) VALUES
(8306, 'etodolac', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Diuretics Etodolac has no apparent pharmacokinetic interaction when administered with furosemide or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'amantadine hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Coadministration of Dyazide (triamterene/hydrochlorothiazide) resulted in a higher plasma amantadine concentration in a 61-year-old man receiving amantadine 100 mg TID for Parkinson''s disease.1 It is not known which of the components of Dyazide contributed to the observation or if related drugs produce a similar response.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'enalapril maleate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics – potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins – Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins. Single doses of either cholestyramine or colestipol resins bind the hydrochlorothiazide and reduce its absorption from the gastrointestinal tract by up to 85 and 43 percent, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'ketoprofen', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide, given concomitantly with ketoprofen, produces a reduction in urinary potassium and chloride excretion compared to hydrochlorothiazide alone.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'febuxostat', 'N/A', 'major', '7.3 In Vivo Drug Interaction Studies Based on drug interaction studies in healthy subjects, ULORIC does not have clinically significant interactions with colchicine, naproxen, indomethacin, hydrochlorothiazide, warfarin or desipramine [see Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)].', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'pramipexole dihydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Other drugs eliminated via renal secretion: Population pharmacokinetic analysis suggests that coadministration of drugs that are secreted by the cationic transport system (e.g., cimetidine, ranitidine, diltiazem, triamterene, verapamil, quinidine, and quinine) decreases the oral clearance of pramipexole by about 20%, while those secreted by the anionic transport system (e.g., cephalosporins, penicillins, indomethacin, hydrochlorothiazide, and chlorpropamide) are likely to have little effect on the oral clearance of pramipexole.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'losartan potassium and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'There is no pharmacokinetic interaction between losartan and hydrochlorothiazide. Hydrochlorothiazide After oral administration of hydrochlorothiazide, diuresis begins within 2 hours, peaks in about 4 hours and lasts about 6 to 12 hours. Hydrochlorothiazide is not metabolized but is eliminated rapidly by the kidney.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'topiramate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide (HCTZ): A drug-drug interaction study conducted in healthy volunteers evaluated the steady-state pharmacokinetics of HCTZ (25 mg q24h) and topiramate (96 mg q12h) when administered alone and concomitantly.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'valsartan', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when Diovan (valsartan) was coadministered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'lisinopril, arginine', 'N/A', 'major', 'No clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when Lisinopril Tablets were used concomitantly with propranolol or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'losartan potassium', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions No significant drug-drug pharmacokinetic interactions have been found in interaction studies with hydrochlorothiazide, digoxin, warfarin, cimetidine and phenobarbital.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'milrinone lactate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions No untoward clinical manifestations have been observed in limited experience with patients in whom milrinone was used concurrently with the following drugs: digitalis glycosides; lidocaine, quinidine; hydralazine, prazosin; isosorbide dinitrate, nitroglycerin; chlorthalidone, furosemide, hydrochlorothiazide, spironolactone; captopril; heparin, warfarin, diazepam, insulin; and potassium supplements.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'irbesartan', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions No significant drug-drug pharmacokinetic (or pharmacodynamic) interactions have been found in interaction studies with hydrochlorothiazide, digoxin, warfarin, and nifedipine. In separate studies of patients receiving maintenance doses of warfarin, hydrochlorothiazide, or digoxin, irbesartan administration for 7 days had no effect on the pharmacodynamics of warfarin (prothrombin time) or pharmacokinetics of digoxin. The pharmacokinetics of irbesartan were not affected by coadministration of nifedipine or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'amlodipine valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'Valsartan No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was co-administered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin. Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics: Potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins: Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'eprosartan mesylate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Or 800 mg q.d.) doses have been safely used concomitantly with a thiazide diuretic (hydrochlorothiazide). Hydrochlorothiazide: When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics – potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins – Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Valsartan: No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was coadministered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin. Hydrochlorothiazide: When administered concurrently, the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, Barbiturates, or N arcotics - Potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and Colestipol R esins - Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'amlodipine besylate and valsartan', 'N/A', 'major', 'Studies with Valsartan No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was co-administered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'acebutolol hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'major', 'No significant interactions with digoxin, hydrochlorothiazide, hydralazine, sulfinpyrazone, oral contraceptives, tolbutamide, or warfarin have been observed.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'candesartan cilexetil and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions Candesartan Cilexetil No significant drug interactions have been reported in studies of candesartan cilexetil given with other drugs such as glyburide, nifedipine, digoxin, warfarin, hydrochlorothiazide, and oral contraceptives in healthy volunteers. Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics − Potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins − Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'telmisartan', 'N/A', 'major', 'Other Drugs: Co-administration of telmisartan did not result in a clinically significant interaction with acetaminophen, amlodipine, glyburide, simvastatin, hydrochlorothiazide, warfarin, or ibuprofen.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'telmisartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'Because lithium should not be used with diuretics, the use of lithium with telmisartan and hydrochlorothiazide is not recommended. Other Drugs: Co-administration of telmisartan did not result in a clinically significant interaction with acetaminophen, amlodipine, glibenclamide, simvastatin, hydrochlorothiazide or ibuprofen. Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently, the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics: Potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'benazepril hydrochloride and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Cholestyramine and colestipol resins: Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins. Single doses of either cholestyramine or colestipol resins bind the hydrochlorothiazide and reduce its absorption from the gastrointestinal tract by up to 85% and 43%, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'betaxolol', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions The following drugs have been coadministered with betaxolol and have not altered its pharmacokinetics: cimetidine, nifedipine, chlorthalidone, and hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'fluconazole', 'N/A', 'contraindicated', 'These are described in greater detail below: Oral hypoglycemics Coumarin-type anticoagulants Phenytoin Cyclosporine Rifampin Theophylline Terfenadine Cisapride Astemizole Rifabutin Voriconazole Tacrolimus Short-acting benzodiazepines Triazolam Oral Contraceptives Pimozide Hydrochlorothiazide Alfentanil Amitriptyline, nortriptyline Amphotericin B Azithromycin Carbamazepine Calcium Channel Blockers Celecoxib Cyclophosphamide Fentanyl Halofantrine HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors Losartan Methadone Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs Prednisone Saquinavir Sirolimus Vinca Alkaloids Vitamin A Zidovudine Oral hypoglycemics: Clinically significant hypoglycemia may be precipitated by the use of fluconazole with oral hypoglycemic agents; one fatality has been reported from hypoglycemia in association', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'fosinopril sodium', 'N/A', 'minor', 'In separate single or multiple dose pharmacokinetic interaction studies with chlorthalidone, nifedipine, propranolol, hydrochlorothiazide, cimetidine, metoclopramide, propantheline, digoxin, and warfarin, the bioavailability of fosinoprilat was not altered by coadministration of fosinopril with any one of these drugs.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'candesartan cilexetil', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No significant drug interactions have been reported in studies of candesartan cilexetil given with other drugs such as glyburide, nifedipine, digoxin, warfarin, hydrochlorothiazide, and oral contraceptives in healthy volunteers, or given with enalapril to patients with heart failure (NYHA class II and III).', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'losartan potatssium', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions No significant drug-drug pharmacokinetic interactions have been found in interaction studies with hydrochlorothiazide, digoxin, warfarin, cimetidine and phenobarbital.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'terazosin', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Terazosin has been used concomitantly in at least 50 patients on the following drugs or drug classes: 1) analgesic/anti-inflammatory (e.g., acetaminophen, aspirin, codeine, ibuprofen, indomethacin); 2) antibiotics (e.g., erythromycin, trimethoprim and sulfamethoxazole); 3) anticholinergic/sympathomimetics (e.g., phenylephrine hydrochloride, phenylpropanolamine hydrochloride, pseudoephedrine hydrochloride); 4) antigout (e.g., allopurinol); 5) antihistamines (e.g., chlorpheniramine); 6) cardiovascular agents (e.g., atenolol, hydrochlorothiazide, methyclothiazide, propranolol); 7) corticosteroids; 8) gastrointestinal agents (e.g., antacids); 9) hypoglycemics; 10) sedatives and tranquilizers (e.g., diazepam).', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'carbamazepine', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Concomitant medication with carbamazepine and some diuretics (hydrochlorothiazide, furosemide) may lead to symptomatic hyponatremia.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'quinapril hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'No pharmacokinetic interaction was observed when single doses of quinapril hydrochloride and hydrochlorothiazide were administered concomitantly.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'isradipine', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Nitroglycerin: A study in normal healthy volunteers has shown that concomitant administration of isradipine and hydrochlorothiazide does not result in altered pharmacokinetics of either drug. In a study in hypertensive patients, addition of isradipine to existing hydrochlorothiazide therapy did not result in any unexpected adverse effects, and isradipine had an additional antihypertensive effect. Hydrochlorothiazide: In a single dose study in normal volunteers, co-administration of propranolol had a small effect on the rate but no effect on the extent of isradipine bioavailability.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'amlodipine and valsartan', 'N/A', 'major', 'Studies with Valsartan No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was co-administered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'quinapril hydrochloride and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Drug Interactions Agents Increasing Serum Potassium: Coadministration of quinapril HCl and hydrochlorothiazide tablets with other drugs that raise serum potassium levels may result in hyperkalemia. Because renal clearance of lithium is reduced by thiazides, the risk of lithium toxicity is presumably raised further when, as in therapy with quinapril HCl and hydrochlorothiazide tablets, a thiazide diuretic is coadministered with the ACE inhibitor. Quinapril HCl and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and lithium should be coadministered with caution, and frequent monitoring of serum lithium levels is recommended.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'memantine hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', '7.4 Drugs Eliminated via Renal Mechanisms Because memantine is eliminated in part by tubular secretion, coadministration of drugs that use the same renal cationic system, including hydrochlorothiazide (HCTZ), triamterene (TA), metformin, cimetidine, ranitidine, quinidine, and nicotine, could potentially result in altered plasma levels of both agents.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'pindolol', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Pindolol has been used with a variety of antihypertensive agents, including hydrochlorothiazide, hydralazine, and guanethidine without unexpected adverse interactions.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'diflunisal', 'N/A', 'major', 'In normal volunteers, concomitant administration of diflunisal and hydrochlorothiazide resulted in significantly increased plasma levels of hydrochlorothiazide. Diflunisal decreased the hyperuricemic effect of hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'moexipril hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'major', 'Other Agents No clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when moexipril hydrochloride was administered concomitantly with hydrochlorothiazide, digoxin, or cimetidine.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'doxazosin', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Doxazosin tablets have been used with the following drugs or drug classes: 1) analgesic/anti-inflammatory (e.g., acetaminophen, aspirin, codeine and codeine combinations, ibuprofen, indomethacin); 2) antibiotics (e.g., erythromycin, trimethoprim and sulfamethoxazole, amoxicillin); 3) antihistamines (e.g., chlorpheniramine); 4) cardiovascular agents (e.g., atenolol, hydrochlorothiazide, propranolol); 5) corticosteroids; 6) gastrointestinal agents (e.g., antacids); 7) hypoglycemics and endocrine drugs; 8) sedatives and tranquilizers (e.g., diazepam); 9) cold and flu remedies.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'fluconazole, sodium chloride', 'N/A', 'contraindicated', 'These are described in greater detail below: Oral hypoglycemics Coumarin-type anticoagulants Phenytoin Cyclosporine Rifampin Theophylline Terfenadine Cisapride Astemizole Rifabutin Voriconazole Tacrolimus Short-acting benzodiazepines Tofacitinib Triazolam Oral Contraceptives Pimozide Quinidine Hydrochlorothiazide Alfentanil Amitriptyline, nortriptyline Amphotericin B Azithromycin Carbamazepine Calcium Channel Blockers Celecoxib Cyclophosphamide Fentanyl Halofantrine HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors Losartan Methadone Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs Prednisone Saquinavir Sirolimus Vinca Alkaloids Vitamin A Zidovudine Oral hypoglycemics Clinically significant hypoglycemia may be precipitated by the use of fluconazole with oral hypoglycemic agents; one fatality has been reported from hypogl', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine besylate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Increased exposure to cyclosporin and tacrolimus Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide (7.3): Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [See Contraindications ( 4 )].', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'dofetilide', 'N/A', 'contraindicated', 'Hydrochlorothiazide (HCTZ) Alone or in Combination with Triamterene (see CONTRAINDICATIONS ) Concomitant use of HCTZ alone or in combination with triamterene is contraindicated.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'olmesartan medoxomil-hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Lithium: Risk of lithium toxicity (7.2) Non-Steroidal Anti-Inflammatory Drugs (NSAIDs): Reduced diuretic, natriuretic and antihypotensive effects; increased risk of renal toxicity (7.3) Dual inhibition of the renin-angiotensin system: Increased risk of renal impairment, hypotension, and hyperkalemia (7.4) Colesevelam hydrochloride: Consider administering olmesartan at least 4 hours before colesevelam hydrochloride dose (7.5) Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment may be required (7.6) Cholestyramine and colestipol: Reduced absorption of thiazides (7.6) 7.1 Agents Increasing Serum Potassium Coadministration of olmesartan medoxomil and hydrochlorothiazide tablets with other drugs that raise serum potassium levels may result in hyperkalemia. 7.2 Lithium Increases in serum l', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'losartan pot/hctz', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Monitor lithium levels in patients receiving losartan potassium and hydrochlorothiazide and lithium. Hydrochlorothiazide The administration of a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory agent including a selective COX-2 inhibitor can reduce the diuretic, natriuretic, and antihypertensive effects of loop, potassium-sparing and thiazide diuretics. Therefore, when losartan potassium and hydrochlorothiazide and non-steroidal anti-inflammatory agents including selective COX-2 inhibitors are used concomitantly, observe closely to determine if the desired effect of the diuretic is obtained.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'fosinopirl sodium', 'N/A', 'minor', 'In separate single or multiple dose pharmacokinetic interaction studies with chlorthalidone, nifedipine, propranolol, hydrochlorothiazide, cimetidine, metoclopramide, propantheline, digoxin, and warfarin, the bioavailability of fosinoprilat was not altered by coadministration of fosinopril with any one of these drugs.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'lithium carbonate', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Reduce lithium dosage based on serum lithium concentration and clinical response [see Dosage and Administration (2.6), Warning and Precautions (5.3)] Examples: hydrochlorothiazide, chlorothiazide, furosemide Non-Steroidal Anti-inflammatory Drugs (NSAID) Clinical Impact: NSAID decrease renal blood flow, resulting in decreased renal clearance and increased serum lithium concentrations.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'In general, avoid combined use of RAS inhibitors, closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes. Avoid use of aliskiren with lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with renal impairment (GFR < 60 ml/min).', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'olmesartan medoxomil and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS • Lithium: Risk of lithium toxicity (7.2) • Non-Steroidal Anti-Inflammatory Drugs (NSAIDs): Reduced diuretic, natriuretic and antihypotensive effects; increased risk of renal toxicity (7.3) • Dual inhibition of the renin-angiotensin system: Increased risk of renal impairment, hypotension, and hyperkalemia (7.4) • Colesevelam hydrochloride: Consider administering olmesartan at least 4 hours before colesevelam hydrochloride dose (7.5) • Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment may be required (7.6) • Cholestyramine and colestipol: Reduced absorption of thiazides (7.6) 7.1 Agents Increasing Serum Potassium Coadministration of olmesartan medoxomil and hydrochlorothiazide tablets with other drugs that raise serum potassium levels may result in hyperkalemia. 7.2 Lithium Increase', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'milrinone lactate in dextrose', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions No untoward clinical manifestations have been observed in limited experience with patients in whom Milrinone was used concurrently with the following drugs: digitalis glycosides; lidocaine, quinidine; hydralazine, prazosin; isosorbide dinitrate, nitroglycerin; chlorthalidone, furosemide, hydrochlorothiazide, spironolactone; captopril; heparin, warfarin, diazepam, insulin; and potassium supplements.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'metoprolol tartrate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide: Hypokalemia can sensitize or exaggerate the response of the heart to the toxic effects of digitalis (e.g., increased ventricular irritability). There have been rare reports in the literature of hemolytic anemia occurring with the concomitant use of hydrochlorothiazide and methyldopa. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins: Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'fosinopril', 'N/A', 'minor', 'In separate single or multiple dose pharmacokinetic interaction studies with chlorthalidone, nifedipine, propranolol, hydrochlorothiazide, cimetidine, metoclopramide, propantheline, digoxin, and warfarin, the bioavailability of fosinoprilat was not altered by coadministration of fosinopril with any one of these drugs.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'telmisartan and amlodipine', 'N/A', 'major', 'Other Drugs: Co-administration of telmisartan did not result in a clinically significant interaction with acetaminophen, amlodipine, glyburide, simvastatin, hydrochlorothiazide, warfarin, or ibuprofen.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'amantadine', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Coadministration of triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide capsules resulted in a higher plasma amantadine concentration in a 61-year-old man receiving amantadine (hydrochloride capsules) 100 mg t.i.d. It is not known which of the components of triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide capsules contributed to the observation or if related drugs produce a similar response.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'captopril and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Gold: Nitritoid reactions (symptoms include facial flushing, nausea, vomiting and hypotension) have been reported rarely in patients on therapy with injectable gold (sodium aurothiomalate) and concomitant ACE inhibitor therapy including captopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets. If a diuretic is also used, it may increase the risk of lithium toxicity (see PRECAUTIONS: Drug Interactions: Hydrochlorothiazide: Lithium ). Hydrochlorothiazide: When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, Barbiturates, or Narcotics: potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'spironolactone and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Pressor Amines (e.g., norepinephrine) Both spironolactone and hydrochlorothiazide reduce the vascular responsiveness to norepinephrine. Therefore, caution should be exercised in the management of patients subjected to regional or general anesthesia while they are being treated with spironolactone and hydrochlorothiazide. Therefore, when spironolactone and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and NSAIDs are used concomitantly, the patient should be observed closely to determine if the desired effect of the diuretic is obtained.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'milrinone lactate in 5% dextrose', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions No untoward clinical manifestations have been observed in limited experience with patients in whom milrinone was used concurrently with the following drugs: digitalis glycosides; lidocaine, quinidine; hydralazine, prazosin; isosorbide dinitrate, nitroglycerin; chlorthalidone, furosemide, hydrochlorothiazide, spironolactone; captopril; heparin, warfarin, diazepam, insulin; and potassium supplements.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'olmesartan medoxomil / amlodipine besylate / hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide ( 7.3): Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. 3 Drug Interactions with Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Antidiabetic Drugs (oral agents and insulin): Dosage adjustment of the antidiabetic drug may be required. Cholestyramine and Colestipol Resins: Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'valsartan/htcz', 'N/A', 'major', 'Valsartan-Hydrochlorothiazide: Lithium: Increases in serum lithium concentrations and lithium toxicity have been reported during concomitant administration of lithium with angiotensin II receptor antagonists or thiazides. Valsartan: No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was coadministered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'amiloride hydrochloride and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Therefore, when amiloride and hydrochlorothiazide plus non-steroidal anti-inflammatory agents are used concomitantly, the patient should be observed closely to determine if the desired effect of the diuretic is obtained. Hydrochlorothiazide When given concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics. Cholestyramine and Colestipol Resins Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'febuxostat tablets 40 mg', 'N/A', 'major', '7.3 In Vivo Drug Interaction Studies Based on drug interaction studies in healthy patients, febuxostat does not have clinically significant interactions with colchicine, naproxen, indomethacin, hydrochlorothiazide, warfarin or desipramine [see Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)].', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'dapagliflozin', 'N/A', 'minor', 'No dosing adjustments required for the following: Oral Antidiabetic Agents Metformin (1000 mg) 20 mg ↔ ↔ Pioglitazone (45 mg) 50 mg ↔ ↔ Sitagliptin (100 mg) 20 mg ↔ ↔ Glimepiride (4 mg) 20 mg ↔ ↔ Voglibose (0.2 mg three times daily) 10 mg ↔ ↔ Other Medications Hydrochlorothiazide (25 mg) 50 mg ↔ ↔ Bumetanide (1 mg) 10 mg once dailyfor 7 days ↔ ↔ Valsartan (320 mg) 20 mg ↓12%[↓3%, ↓20%] ↔ Simvastatin (40 mg) 20 mg ↔ ↔ Anti-infective Agent Rifampin (600 mg once daily for 6 days) 10 mg ↓7%[↓22%, ↑11%] ↓22%[↓27%, ↓17%] Nonsteroidal Anti-inflammatory Agent Mefenamic Acid (loading dose of 500 mg followed by 14 doses of 250 mg every 6 hours) 10 mg ↑13%[↑3%, ↑24%] ↑51%[↑44%, ↑58%] ↔ = no change (geometric mean ratio of test: reference within 0.80 to 1.25); ↓ or ↑ = parameter was lower or higher, r', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No drug interaction studies have been conducted with amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide and other drugs, although studies have been conducted with the individual components. A pharmacokinetic drug-drug interaction study has been conducted to address the potential for pharmacokinetic interaction between the triple combination, amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide, and the corresponding 3 double combinations. Valsartan-Hydrochlorothiazide Lithium Increases in serum lithium concentrations and lithium toxicity have been reported during concomitant administration of lithium with angiotensin II receptor antagonists or thiazides.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'sotalol hydrochloride tables af', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Other No pharmacokinetic interactions were observed with hydrochlorothiazide or warfarin.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'quinapril hydrochloride/hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Drug Interactions Agents Increasing Serum Potassium Coadministration of quinapril and hydrochlorothiazide with other drugs that raise serum potassium levels may result in hyperkalemia. Because renal clearance of lithium is reduced by thiazides, the risk of lithium toxicity is presumably raised further when, as in therapy with quinapril and hydrochlorothiazide, a thiazide diuretic is coadministered with the ACE inhibitor. Quinapril and hydrochlorothiazide and lithium should be coadministered with caution, and frequent monitoring of serum lithium levels is recommended.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'amlodipine,valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No drug interaction studies have been conducted with amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other drugs, although studies have been conducted with the individual components. A pharmacokinetic drug-drug interaction study has been conducted to address the potential for pharmacokinetic interaction between the triple combination, amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide tablets, and the corresponding 3 double combinations. Valsartan – Hydrochlorothiazide Lithium: Increases in serum lithium concentrations and lithium toxicity have been reported during concomitant administration of lithium with angiotensin II receptor antagonists or thiazides.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'amlodipine besylate valsartan hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No drug interaction studies have been conducted with amlodipine/valsartan/hydrochlorothiazide and other drugs, although studies have been conducted with the individual components. A pharmacokinetic drug-drug interaction study has been conducted to address the potential for pharmacokinetic interaction between the triple combination, amlodipine/valsartan/hydrochlorothiazide, and the corresponding 3 double combinations. Valsartan – Hydrochlorothiazide Lithium: Increases in serum lithium concentrations and lithium toxicity have been reported during concomitant administration of lithium with angiotensin II receptor antagonists or thiazides.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'phentermine and topiramate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Concomitant administration of hydrochlorothiazide alone with topiramate alone has been shown to increase the C max and AUC of topiramate by 27% and 29%, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide (7.3): Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine, and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not coadminister aliskiren with olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine, and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [see Contraindications (4)].', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'tolterodine tartrate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Diuretics Coadministration of tolterodine immediate release up to 8 mg (4 mg bid) for up to 12 weeks with diuretic agents, such as indapamide, hydrochlorothiazide, triamterene, bendroflumethiazide, chlorothiazide, methylchlorothiazide, or furosemide, did not cause any adverse electrocardiographic (ECG) effects.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'phentermine and topiramate extended-release', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Concomitant administration of hydrochlorothiazide alone with topiramate alone has been shown to increase the Cmax and AUC of topiramate by 27% and 29%, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'topiramate spinkle', 'N/A', 'minor', '7.5 Hydrochlorothiazide (HCTZ) Topiramate Cmax and AUC increased when HCTZ was added to topiramate.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'fluconazole in sodium chloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide In a pharmacokinetic interaction study, coadministration of multiple-dose hydrochlorothiazide to healthy volunteers receiving fluconazole increased plasma concentrations of fluconazole by 40%.', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablet 20/5/12.5 mg', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Increased exposure to cyclosporin and tacrolimus Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide ( 7.3): Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on Olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with Olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [See Contraindications ( 4)].', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'olmesartan medoxomil and amlodipine besylate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', '•Increased exposure to cyclosporin and tacrolimus •Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide (7.3): •Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine, and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine, and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [See Contraindications (4)].', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'olmesartan medoxomil amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', '• Increased exposure to cyclosporin and tacrolimus • Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide (7.3): • Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [See Contraindications (4 )].', 'DailyMed'),
(8306, 'sucroferric oxyhydroxide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Table 1 Oral drugs that can be administered concomitantly with Velphoro Calcitriol Ciprofloxacin Digoxin Enalapril Furosemide HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide Losartan Metoprolol Nifedipine Omeprazole Quinidine Warfarin Oral drugs that are to be separated from Velphoro Dosing Recommendations Doxycycline Acetylsalicylic acid Cephalexin Take at least 1 hour before Velphoro. Levothyroxine Take at least 4 hours before Velphoro Velphoro can be administered concomitantly with oral calcitriol, ciprofloxacin, digoxin, enalapril, furosemide, HMG‑CoA reductase inhibitors, hydrochlorothiazide, losartan, metoprolol, nifedipine, omeprazole, quinidine and warfarin.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'sotalol hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Other No pharmacokinetic interactions were observed with hydrochlorothiazide or warfarin.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'bisoprolol fumarate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Drug interactions Bisoprolol and hydrochlorothiazide may potentiate the action of other antihypertensive agents used concomitantly. Bisoprolol and hydrochlorothiazide should not be combined with other beta-blocking agents. In patients receiving concurrent therapy with clonidine, if therapy is to be discontinued, it is suggested that bisoprolol and hydrochlorothiazide be discontinued for several days before the withdrawal of clonidine.Bisoprolol and hydrochlorothiazide should be used with caution when myocardial depressants or inhibitors of AV conduction, such as certain calcium antagonists [particularly of the phenylalkylamine (verapamil) and benzothiazepine (diltiazem) classes], or antiarrhythmic agents, such as disopyramide, are used concurrently.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'sotalol', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Other No pharmacokinetic interactions were observed with hydrochlorothiazide or warfarin.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions When given concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics.Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcoticsPotentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur.Antidiabetic drugs - (oral agents and insulin)Dosage adjustment of the antidiabetic drug may be required.Other antihypertensive drugsAdditive effect or potentiation.Cholestryamine and colestipol resinsAbsorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins. Single doses of either cholestyramine or colestipol resins bind the hydrochlorothiazide and reduce its absorption from the gastrointestinal tract by up to 85 and 43 percent, respectively.Corticosteroids, ACTHIntensified electrolyte depletion, particularly hypokalemia.Pressor amines (e.g., norepinephrine)Possible decreased r', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'No meaningful clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when lisinopril was used concomitantly with propranolol, digoxin, or hydrochlorothiazide. It is recommended that serum lithium levels be monitored frequently if lisinopril is administered concomitantly with lithium.Hydrochlorothiazide: When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics.Alcohol, Barbiturates, Or Narcotics— potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur.Antidiabetic Drugs (Oral Agents And Insulin) — dosage adjustment of the antidiabetic drug may be required.Other Antihypertensive Drugs — additive effect or potentiation.Cholestyramine And Colestipol Resins — Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins. Single doses of ei', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Acute renal failure has been reported in a few patients receiving indomethacin and formulations containing triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide. Caution is therefore advised when administering nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory agents with triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'doxazosin mesylate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Doxazosin mesylate tablets have been used with the following drugs or drug classes: 1) analgesic/anti-inflammatory (e.g., acetaminophen, aspirin, codeine and codeine combinations, ibuprofen, indomethacin); 2) antibiotics (e.g., erythromycin, trimethoprim and sulfamethoxazole, amoxicillin); 3) antihistamines (e.g., chlorpheniramine); 4) cardiovascular agents (e.g., atenolol, hydrochlorothiazide, propranolol); 5) corticosteroids; 6) gastrointestinal agents (e.g., antacids); 7) hypoglycemics and endocrine drugs; 8) sedatives and tranquilizers (e.g., diazepam); 9) cold and flu remedies.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'benazepril hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'major', 'Other No clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when benazepril hydrochloride tablets were administered concomitantly with hydrochlorothiazide, chlorthalidone, furosemide, digoxin, propranolol, atenolol, naproxen, or cimetidine.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'fosinopril sodium and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions Potassium supplements and potassium-sparing diuretics: As noted above ("Derangements of Serum Electrolytes"), the net effect of fosinopril sodium and hydrochlorothiazide may be to elevate a patient''s serum potassium, to reduce it, or to leave it unchanged. Because renal clearance of lithium is reduced by thiazides, the risk of lithium toxicity is presumably raised further when, as in therapy with fosinopril sodium and hydrochlorothiazide tablets, a thiazide diuretic is coadministered with the ACE inhibitor. Other ACE inhibitors have had less than additive effects with betaadrenergic blockers, presumably because drugs of both classes lower blood pressure by inhibiting parts of the renin-angiotensin system.Interaction studies with warfarin have failed to identify any clinic', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'quinapril', 'N/A', 'minor', 'No pharmacokinetic interaction was observed when single doses of quinapril hydrochloride andhydrochlorothiazide were administered concomitantly.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'lisinopril', 'N/A', 'major', 'No clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when lisinopril was used concomitantly with propranolol or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'terazosin hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Terazosin has been used concomitantly in at least 50 patients on the following drugs or drug classes: 1) analgesic/anti-inflammatory (e.g., acetaminophen, aspirin, codeine, ibuprofen, indomethacin); 2) antibiotics (e.g., erythromycin, trimethoprim and sulfamethoxazole); 3) anticholinergic/sympathomimetics (e.g., phenylephrine hydrochloride, phenylpropanolamine hydrochloride, pseudoephedrine hydrochloride); 4) antigout (e.g., allopurinol); 5) antihistamines (e.g., chlorpheniramine); 6) cardiovascular agents (e.g., atenolol, hydrochlorothiazide, methyclothiazide, propranolol); 7) corticosteroids; 8) gastrointestinal agents (e.g., antacids); 9) hypoglycemics; 10) sedatives and tranquilizers (e.g., diazepam).', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'drug_class', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions When given concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'irbesartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '[See Clinical Pharmacology (12.3).] Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, Barbiturates, or Narcotics: potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and Colestipol Resins: absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins. Single doses of either cholestyramine or colestipol resins bind the hydrochlorothiazide and reduce its absorption from the gastrointestinal tract by up to 85% and 43%, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'carvedilol phosphate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide A single oral dose of carvedilol 25 mg did not alter the pharmacokinetics of a single oral dose of hydrochlorothiazide 25 mg in 12 patients with hypertension. Likewise, hydrochlorothiazide had no effect on the pharmacokinetics of carvedilol.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'colestipol hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'major', 'The absorption of tetracycline, furosemide, penicillin G, hydrochlorothiazide, and gemfibrozil was significantly decreased when given simultaneously with colestipol hydrochloride; these drugs were not tested to determine the effect of administration one hour before colestipol hydrochloride.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'aliskiren hemifumarate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No drug interaction studies have been conducted with Tekturna HCT and other drugs, although studies with the individual aliskiren and hydrochlorothiazide components are described below. Drugs with no clinically significant effects: Coadministration of lovastatin, atenolol, warfarin, furosemide, digoxin, celecoxib, hydrochlorothiazide, ramipril, valsartan, metformin and amlodipine did not result in clinically significant increases in aliskiren exposure. Drugs with no clinically significant effects: Coadministration of aliskiren did not significantly affect the pharmacokinetics of lovastatin, digoxin, valsartan, amlodipine, metformin, celecoxib, atenolol, atorvastatin, ramipril or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'etodolac', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Diuretics Etodolac has no apparent pharmacokinetic interaction when administered with furosemide or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'amantadine hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Coadministration of Dyazide (triamterene/hydrochlorothiazide) resulted in a higher plasma amantadine concentration in a 61-year-old man receiving amantadine 100 mg TID for Parkinson''s disease.1 It is not known which of the components of Dyazide contributed to the observation or if related drugs produce a similar response.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'enalapril maleate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics – potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins – Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins. Single doses of either cholestyramine or colestipol resins bind the hydrochlorothiazide and reduce its absorption from the gastrointestinal tract by up to 85 and 43 percent, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'ketoprofen', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide, given concomitantly with ketoprofen, produces a reduction in urinary potassium and chloride excretion compared to hydrochlorothiazide alone.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'febuxostat', 'N/A', 'major', '7.3 In Vivo Drug Interaction Studies Based on drug interaction studies in healthy subjects, ULORIC does not have clinically significant interactions with colchicine, naproxen, indomethacin, hydrochlorothiazide, warfarin or desipramine [see Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)].', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'pramipexole dihydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Other drugs eliminated via renal secretion: Population pharmacokinetic analysis suggests that coadministration of drugs that are secreted by the cationic transport system (e.g., cimetidine, ranitidine, diltiazem, triamterene, verapamil, quinidine, and quinine) decreases the oral clearance of pramipexole by about 20%, while those secreted by the anionic transport system (e.g., cephalosporins, penicillins, indomethacin, hydrochlorothiazide, and chlorpropamide) are likely to have little effect on the oral clearance of pramipexole.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'losartan potassium and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'There is no pharmacokinetic interaction between losartan and hydrochlorothiazide. Hydrochlorothiazide After oral administration of hydrochlorothiazide, diuresis begins within 2 hours, peaks in about 4 hours and lasts about 6 to 12 hours. Hydrochlorothiazide is not metabolized but is eliminated rapidly by the kidney.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'topiramate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide (HCTZ): A drug-drug interaction study conducted in healthy volunteers evaluated the steady-state pharmacokinetics of HCTZ (25 mg q24h) and topiramate (96 mg q12h) when administered alone and concomitantly.', 'DailyMed');
INSERT INTO drug_interactions (med_id, interaction_drug_name, interaction_dailymed_id, severity, description, source) VALUES
(22059, 'valsartan', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when Diovan (valsartan) was coadministered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'lisinopril, arginine', 'N/A', 'major', 'No clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when Lisinopril Tablets were used concomitantly with propranolol or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'losartan potassium', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions No significant drug-drug pharmacokinetic interactions have been found in interaction studies with hydrochlorothiazide, digoxin, warfarin, cimetidine and phenobarbital.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'milrinone lactate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions No untoward clinical manifestations have been observed in limited experience with patients in whom milrinone was used concurrently with the following drugs: digitalis glycosides; lidocaine, quinidine; hydralazine, prazosin; isosorbide dinitrate, nitroglycerin; chlorthalidone, furosemide, hydrochlorothiazide, spironolactone; captopril; heparin, warfarin, diazepam, insulin; and potassium supplements.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'irbesartan', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions No significant drug-drug pharmacokinetic (or pharmacodynamic) interactions have been found in interaction studies with hydrochlorothiazide, digoxin, warfarin, and nifedipine. In separate studies of patients receiving maintenance doses of warfarin, hydrochlorothiazide, or digoxin, irbesartan administration for 7 days had no effect on the pharmacodynamics of warfarin (prothrombin time) or pharmacokinetics of digoxin. The pharmacokinetics of irbesartan were not affected by coadministration of nifedipine or hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'amlodipine valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'Valsartan No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was co-administered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin. Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics: Potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins: Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'eprosartan mesylate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Or 800 mg q.d.) doses have been safely used concomitantly with a thiazide diuretic (hydrochlorothiazide). Hydrochlorothiazide: When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics – potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins – Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Valsartan: No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was coadministered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin. Hydrochlorothiazide: When administered concurrently, the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, Barbiturates, or N arcotics - Potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and Colestipol R esins - Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'amlodipine besylate and valsartan', 'N/A', 'major', 'Studies with Valsartan No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was co-administered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'acebutolol hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'major', 'No significant interactions with digoxin, hydrochlorothiazide, hydralazine, sulfinpyrazone, oral contraceptives, tolbutamide, or warfarin have been observed.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'candesartan cilexetil and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions Candesartan Cilexetil No significant drug interactions have been reported in studies of candesartan cilexetil given with other drugs such as glyburide, nifedipine, digoxin, warfarin, hydrochlorothiazide, and oral contraceptives in healthy volunteers. Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics − Potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins − Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'telmisartan', 'N/A', 'major', 'Other Drugs: Co-administration of telmisartan did not result in a clinically significant interaction with acetaminophen, amlodipine, glyburide, simvastatin, hydrochlorothiazide, warfarin, or ibuprofen.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'telmisartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'major', 'Because lithium should not be used with diuretics, the use of lithium with telmisartan and hydrochlorothiazide is not recommended. Other Drugs: Co-administration of telmisartan did not result in a clinically significant interaction with acetaminophen, amlodipine, glibenclamide, simvastatin, hydrochlorothiazide or ibuprofen. Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently, the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, barbiturates, or narcotics: Potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'benazepril hydrochloride and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Cholestyramine and colestipol resins: Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins. Single doses of either cholestyramine or colestipol resins bind the hydrochlorothiazide and reduce its absorption from the gastrointestinal tract by up to 85% and 43%, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'betaxolol', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions The following drugs have been coadministered with betaxolol and have not altered its pharmacokinetics: cimetidine, nifedipine, chlorthalidone, and hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'fluconazole', 'N/A', 'contraindicated', 'These are described in greater detail below: Oral hypoglycemics Coumarin-type anticoagulants Phenytoin Cyclosporine Rifampin Theophylline Terfenadine Cisapride Astemizole Rifabutin Voriconazole Tacrolimus Short-acting benzodiazepines Triazolam Oral Contraceptives Pimozide Hydrochlorothiazide Alfentanil Amitriptyline, nortriptyline Amphotericin B Azithromycin Carbamazepine Calcium Channel Blockers Celecoxib Cyclophosphamide Fentanyl Halofantrine HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors Losartan Methadone Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs Prednisone Saquinavir Sirolimus Vinca Alkaloids Vitamin A Zidovudine Oral hypoglycemics: Clinically significant hypoglycemia may be precipitated by the use of fluconazole with oral hypoglycemic agents; one fatality has been reported from hypoglycemia in association', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'fosinopril sodium', 'N/A', 'minor', 'In separate single or multiple dose pharmacokinetic interaction studies with chlorthalidone, nifedipine, propranolol, hydrochlorothiazide, cimetidine, metoclopramide, propantheline, digoxin, and warfarin, the bioavailability of fosinoprilat was not altered by coadministration of fosinopril with any one of these drugs.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'candesartan cilexetil', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No significant drug interactions have been reported in studies of candesartan cilexetil given with other drugs such as glyburide, nifedipine, digoxin, warfarin, hydrochlorothiazide, and oral contraceptives in healthy volunteers, or given with enalapril to patients with heart failure (NYHA class II and III).', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'losartan potatssium', 'N/A', 'major', 'Drug Interactions No significant drug-drug pharmacokinetic interactions have been found in interaction studies with hydrochlorothiazide, digoxin, warfarin, cimetidine and phenobarbital.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'terazosin', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Terazosin has been used concomitantly in at least 50 patients on the following drugs or drug classes: 1) analgesic/anti-inflammatory (e.g., acetaminophen, aspirin, codeine, ibuprofen, indomethacin); 2) antibiotics (e.g., erythromycin, trimethoprim and sulfamethoxazole); 3) anticholinergic/sympathomimetics (e.g., phenylephrine hydrochloride, phenylpropanolamine hydrochloride, pseudoephedrine hydrochloride); 4) antigout (e.g., allopurinol); 5) antihistamines (e.g., chlorpheniramine); 6) cardiovascular agents (e.g., atenolol, hydrochlorothiazide, methyclothiazide, propranolol); 7) corticosteroids; 8) gastrointestinal agents (e.g., antacids); 9) hypoglycemics; 10) sedatives and tranquilizers (e.g., diazepam).', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'carbamazepine', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Concomitant medication with carbamazepine and some diuretics (hydrochlorothiazide, furosemide) may lead to symptomatic hyponatremia.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'quinapril hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'No pharmacokinetic interaction was observed when single doses of quinapril hydrochloride and hydrochlorothiazide were administered concomitantly.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'isradipine', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Nitroglycerin: A study in normal healthy volunteers has shown that concomitant administration of isradipine and hydrochlorothiazide does not result in altered pharmacokinetics of either drug. In a study in hypertensive patients, addition of isradipine to existing hydrochlorothiazide therapy did not result in any unexpected adverse effects, and isradipine had an additional antihypertensive effect. Hydrochlorothiazide: In a single dose study in normal volunteers, co-administration of propranolol had a small effect on the rate but no effect on the extent of isradipine bioavailability.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'amlodipine and valsartan', 'N/A', 'major', 'Studies with Valsartan No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was co-administered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'quinapril hydrochloride and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Drug Interactions Agents Increasing Serum Potassium: Coadministration of quinapril HCl and hydrochlorothiazide tablets with other drugs that raise serum potassium levels may result in hyperkalemia. Because renal clearance of lithium is reduced by thiazides, the risk of lithium toxicity is presumably raised further when, as in therapy with quinapril HCl and hydrochlorothiazide tablets, a thiazide diuretic is coadministered with the ACE inhibitor. Quinapril HCl and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and lithium should be coadministered with caution, and frequent monitoring of serum lithium levels is recommended.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'memantine hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', '7.4 Drugs Eliminated via Renal Mechanisms Because memantine is eliminated in part by tubular secretion, coadministration of drugs that use the same renal cationic system, including hydrochlorothiazide (HCTZ), triamterene (TA), metformin, cimetidine, ranitidine, quinidine, and nicotine, could potentially result in altered plasma levels of both agents.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'pindolol', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Pindolol has been used with a variety of antihypertensive agents, including hydrochlorothiazide, hydralazine, and guanethidine without unexpected adverse interactions.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'diflunisal', 'N/A', 'major', 'In normal volunteers, concomitant administration of diflunisal and hydrochlorothiazide resulted in significantly increased plasma levels of hydrochlorothiazide. Diflunisal decreased the hyperuricemic effect of hydrochlorothiazide.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'moexipril hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'major', 'Other Agents No clinically important pharmacokinetic interactions occurred when moexipril hydrochloride was administered concomitantly with hydrochlorothiazide, digoxin, or cimetidine.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'doxazosin', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Doxazosin tablets have been used with the following drugs or drug classes: 1) analgesic/anti-inflammatory (e.g., acetaminophen, aspirin, codeine and codeine combinations, ibuprofen, indomethacin); 2) antibiotics (e.g., erythromycin, trimethoprim and sulfamethoxazole, amoxicillin); 3) antihistamines (e.g., chlorpheniramine); 4) cardiovascular agents (e.g., atenolol, hydrochlorothiazide, propranolol); 5) corticosteroids; 6) gastrointestinal agents (e.g., antacids); 7) hypoglycemics and endocrine drugs; 8) sedatives and tranquilizers (e.g., diazepam); 9) cold and flu remedies.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'fluconazole, sodium chloride', 'N/A', 'contraindicated', 'These are described in greater detail below: Oral hypoglycemics Coumarin-type anticoagulants Phenytoin Cyclosporine Rifampin Theophylline Terfenadine Cisapride Astemizole Rifabutin Voriconazole Tacrolimus Short-acting benzodiazepines Tofacitinib Triazolam Oral Contraceptives Pimozide Quinidine Hydrochlorothiazide Alfentanil Amitriptyline, nortriptyline Amphotericin B Azithromycin Carbamazepine Calcium Channel Blockers Celecoxib Cyclophosphamide Fentanyl Halofantrine HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors Losartan Methadone Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs Prednisone Saquinavir Sirolimus Vinca Alkaloids Vitamin A Zidovudine Oral hypoglycemics Clinically significant hypoglycemia may be precipitated by the use of fluconazole with oral hypoglycemic agents; one fatality has been reported from hypogl', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine besylate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Increased exposure to cyclosporin and tacrolimus Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide (7.3): Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [See Contraindications ( 4 )].', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'dofetilide', 'N/A', 'contraindicated', 'Hydrochlorothiazide (HCTZ) Alone or in Combination with Triamterene (see CONTRAINDICATIONS ) Concomitant use of HCTZ alone or in combination with triamterene is contraindicated.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'olmesartan medoxomil-hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Lithium: Risk of lithium toxicity (7.2) Non-Steroidal Anti-Inflammatory Drugs (NSAIDs): Reduced diuretic, natriuretic and antihypotensive effects; increased risk of renal toxicity (7.3) Dual inhibition of the renin-angiotensin system: Increased risk of renal impairment, hypotension, and hyperkalemia (7.4) Colesevelam hydrochloride: Consider administering olmesartan at least 4 hours before colesevelam hydrochloride dose (7.5) Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment may be required (7.6) Cholestyramine and colestipol: Reduced absorption of thiazides (7.6) 7.1 Agents Increasing Serum Potassium Coadministration of olmesartan medoxomil and hydrochlorothiazide tablets with other drugs that raise serum potassium levels may result in hyperkalemia. 7.2 Lithium Increases in serum l', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'losartan pot/hctz', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Monitor lithium levels in patients receiving losartan potassium and hydrochlorothiazide and lithium. Hydrochlorothiazide The administration of a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory agent including a selective COX-2 inhibitor can reduce the diuretic, natriuretic, and antihypertensive effects of loop, potassium-sparing and thiazide diuretics. Therefore, when losartan potassium and hydrochlorothiazide and non-steroidal anti-inflammatory agents including selective COX-2 inhibitors are used concomitantly, observe closely to determine if the desired effect of the diuretic is obtained.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'fosinopirl sodium', 'N/A', 'minor', 'In separate single or multiple dose pharmacokinetic interaction studies with chlorthalidone, nifedipine, propranolol, hydrochlorothiazide, cimetidine, metoclopramide, propantheline, digoxin, and warfarin, the bioavailability of fosinoprilat was not altered by coadministration of fosinopril with any one of these drugs.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'lithium carbonate', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Reduce lithium dosage based on serum lithium concentration and clinical response [see Dosage and Administration (2.6), Warning and Precautions (5.3)] Examples: hydrochlorothiazide, chlorothiazide, furosemide Non-Steroidal Anti-inflammatory Drugs (NSAID) Clinical Impact: NSAID decrease renal blood flow, resulting in decreased renal clearance and increased serum lithium concentrations.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'In general, avoid combined use of RAS inhibitors, closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes. Avoid use of aliskiren with lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with renal impairment (GFR < 60 ml/min).', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'olmesartan medoxomil and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS • Lithium: Risk of lithium toxicity (7.2) • Non-Steroidal Anti-Inflammatory Drugs (NSAIDs): Reduced diuretic, natriuretic and antihypotensive effects; increased risk of renal toxicity (7.3) • Dual inhibition of the renin-angiotensin system: Increased risk of renal impairment, hypotension, and hyperkalemia (7.4) • Colesevelam hydrochloride: Consider administering olmesartan at least 4 hours before colesevelam hydrochloride dose (7.5) • Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment may be required (7.6) • Cholestyramine and colestipol: Reduced absorption of thiazides (7.6) 7.1 Agents Increasing Serum Potassium Coadministration of olmesartan medoxomil and hydrochlorothiazide tablets with other drugs that raise serum potassium levels may result in hyperkalemia. 7.2 Lithium Increase', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'milrinone lactate in dextrose', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions No untoward clinical manifestations have been observed in limited experience with patients in whom Milrinone was used concurrently with the following drugs: digitalis glycosides; lidocaine, quinidine; hydralazine, prazosin; isosorbide dinitrate, nitroglycerin; chlorthalidone, furosemide, hydrochlorothiazide, spironolactone; captopril; heparin, warfarin, diazepam, insulin; and potassium supplements.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'metoprolol tartrate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide: Hypokalemia can sensitize or exaggerate the response of the heart to the toxic effects of digitalis (e.g., increased ventricular irritability). There have been rare reports in the literature of hemolytic anemia occurring with the concomitant use of hydrochlorothiazide and methyldopa. Cholestyramine and colestipol resins: Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'fosinopril', 'N/A', 'minor', 'In separate single or multiple dose pharmacokinetic interaction studies with chlorthalidone, nifedipine, propranolol, hydrochlorothiazide, cimetidine, metoclopramide, propantheline, digoxin, and warfarin, the bioavailability of fosinoprilat was not altered by coadministration of fosinopril with any one of these drugs.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'telmisartan and amlodipine', 'N/A', 'major', 'Other Drugs: Co-administration of telmisartan did not result in a clinically significant interaction with acetaminophen, amlodipine, glyburide, simvastatin, hydrochlorothiazide, warfarin, or ibuprofen.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'amantadine', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Coadministration of triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide capsules resulted in a higher plasma amantadine concentration in a 61-year-old man receiving amantadine (hydrochloride capsules) 100 mg t.i.d. It is not known which of the components of triamterene and hydrochlorothiazide capsules contributed to the observation or if related drugs produce a similar response.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'captopril and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Gold: Nitritoid reactions (symptoms include facial flushing, nausea, vomiting and hypotension) have been reported rarely in patients on therapy with injectable gold (sodium aurothiomalate) and concomitant ACE inhibitor therapy including captopril and hydrochlorothiazide tablets. If a diuretic is also used, it may increase the risk of lithium toxicity (see PRECAUTIONS: Drug Interactions: Hydrochlorothiazide: Lithium ). Hydrochlorothiazide: When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Alcohol, Barbiturates, or Narcotics: potentiation of orthostatic hypotension may occur.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'spironolactone and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Pressor Amines (e.g., norepinephrine) Both spironolactone and hydrochlorothiazide reduce the vascular responsiveness to norepinephrine. Therefore, caution should be exercised in the management of patients subjected to regional or general anesthesia while they are being treated with spironolactone and hydrochlorothiazide. Therefore, when spironolactone and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and NSAIDs are used concomitantly, the patient should be observed closely to determine if the desired effect of the diuretic is obtained.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'milrinone lactate in 5% dextrose', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions No untoward clinical manifestations have been observed in limited experience with patients in whom milrinone was used concurrently with the following drugs: digitalis glycosides; lidocaine, quinidine; hydralazine, prazosin; isosorbide dinitrate, nitroglycerin; chlorthalidone, furosemide, hydrochlorothiazide, spironolactone; captopril; heparin, warfarin, diazepam, insulin; and potassium supplements.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'olmesartan medoxomil / amlodipine besylate / hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide ( 7.3): Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. 3 Drug Interactions with Hydrochlorothiazide When administered concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics: Antidiabetic Drugs (oral agents and insulin): Dosage adjustment of the antidiabetic drug may be required. Cholestyramine and Colestipol Resins: Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'valsartan/htcz', 'N/A', 'major', 'Valsartan-Hydrochlorothiazide: Lithium: Increases in serum lithium concentrations and lithium toxicity have been reported during concomitant administration of lithium with angiotensin II receptor antagonists or thiazides. Valsartan: No clinically significant pharmacokinetic interactions were observed when valsartan was coadministered with amlodipine, atenolol, cimetidine, digoxin, furosemide, glyburide, hydrochlorothiazide, or indomethacin. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'amiloride hydrochloride and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Therefore, when amiloride and hydrochlorothiazide plus non-steroidal anti-inflammatory agents are used concomitantly, the patient should be observed closely to determine if the desired effect of the diuretic is obtained. Hydrochlorothiazide When given concurrently the following drugs may interact with thiazide diuretics. Cholestyramine and Colestipol Resins Absorption of hydrochlorothiazide is impaired in the presence of anionic exchange resins.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'febuxostat tablets 40 mg', 'N/A', 'major', '7.3 In Vivo Drug Interaction Studies Based on drug interaction studies in healthy patients, febuxostat does not have clinically significant interactions with colchicine, naproxen, indomethacin, hydrochlorothiazide, warfarin or desipramine [see Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)].', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'dapagliflozin', 'N/A', 'minor', 'No dosing adjustments required for the following: Oral Antidiabetic Agents Metformin (1000 mg) 20 mg ↔ ↔ Pioglitazone (45 mg) 50 mg ↔ ↔ Sitagliptin (100 mg) 20 mg ↔ ↔ Glimepiride (4 mg) 20 mg ↔ ↔ Voglibose (0.2 mg three times daily) 10 mg ↔ ↔ Other Medications Hydrochlorothiazide (25 mg) 50 mg ↔ ↔ Bumetanide (1 mg) 10 mg once dailyfor 7 days ↔ ↔ Valsartan (320 mg) 20 mg ↓12%[↓3%, ↓20%] ↔ Simvastatin (40 mg) 20 mg ↔ ↔ Anti-infective Agent Rifampin (600 mg once daily for 6 days) 10 mg ↓7%[↓22%, ↑11%] ↓22%[↓27%, ↓17%] Nonsteroidal Anti-inflammatory Agent Mefenamic Acid (loading dose of 500 mg followed by 14 doses of 250 mg every 6 hours) 10 mg ↑13%[↑3%, ↑24%] ↑51%[↑44%, ↑58%] ↔ = no change (geometric mean ratio of test: reference within 0.80 to 1.25); ↓ or ↑ = parameter was lower or higher, r', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No drug interaction studies have been conducted with amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide and other drugs, although studies have been conducted with the individual components. A pharmacokinetic drug-drug interaction study has been conducted to address the potential for pharmacokinetic interaction between the triple combination, amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide, and the corresponding 3 double combinations. Valsartan-Hydrochlorothiazide Lithium Increases in serum lithium concentrations and lithium toxicity have been reported during concomitant administration of lithium with angiotensin II receptor antagonists or thiazides.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'sotalol hydrochloride tables af', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Other No pharmacokinetic interactions were observed with hydrochlorothiazide or warfarin.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'quinapril hydrochloride/hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Drug Interactions Agents Increasing Serum Potassium Coadministration of quinapril and hydrochlorothiazide with other drugs that raise serum potassium levels may result in hyperkalemia. Because renal clearance of lithium is reduced by thiazides, the risk of lithium toxicity is presumably raised further when, as in therapy with quinapril and hydrochlorothiazide, a thiazide diuretic is coadministered with the ACE inhibitor. Quinapril and hydrochlorothiazide and lithium should be coadministered with caution, and frequent monitoring of serum lithium levels is recommended.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'amlodipine,valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No drug interaction studies have been conducted with amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other drugs, although studies have been conducted with the individual components. A pharmacokinetic drug-drug interaction study has been conducted to address the potential for pharmacokinetic interaction between the triple combination, amlodipine, valsartan and hydrochlorothiazide tablets, and the corresponding 3 double combinations. Valsartan – Hydrochlorothiazide Lithium: Increases in serum lithium concentrations and lithium toxicity have been reported during concomitant administration of lithium with angiotensin II receptor antagonists or thiazides.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'amlodipine besylate valsartan hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS No drug interaction studies have been conducted with amlodipine/valsartan/hydrochlorothiazide and other drugs, although studies have been conducted with the individual components. A pharmacokinetic drug-drug interaction study has been conducted to address the potential for pharmacokinetic interaction between the triple combination, amlodipine/valsartan/hydrochlorothiazide, and the corresponding 3 double combinations. Valsartan – Hydrochlorothiazide Lithium: Increases in serum lithium concentrations and lithium toxicity have been reported during concomitant administration of lithium with angiotensin II receptor antagonists or thiazides.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'phentermine and topiramate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Concomitant administration of hydrochlorothiazide alone with topiramate alone has been shown to increase the C max and AUC of topiramate by 27% and 29%, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide (7.3): Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine, and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not coadminister aliskiren with olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine, and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [see Contraindications (4)].', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'tolterodine tartrate', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Diuretics Coadministration of tolterodine immediate release up to 8 mg (4 mg bid) for up to 12 weeks with diuretic agents, such as indapamide, hydrochlorothiazide, triamterene, bendroflumethiazide, chlorothiazide, methylchlorothiazide, or furosemide, did not cause any adverse electrocardiographic (ECG) effects.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'phentermine and topiramate extended-release', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Concomitant administration of hydrochlorothiazide alone with topiramate alone has been shown to increase the Cmax and AUC of topiramate by 27% and 29%, respectively.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'topiramate spinkle', 'N/A', 'minor', '7.5 Hydrochlorothiazide (HCTZ) Topiramate Cmax and AUC increased when HCTZ was added to topiramate.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'fluconazole in sodium chloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Hydrochlorothiazide In a pharmacokinetic interaction study, coadministration of multiple-dose hydrochlorothiazide to healthy volunteers receiving fluconazole increased plasma concentrations of fluconazole by 40%.', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablet 20/5/12.5 mg', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Increased exposure to cyclosporin and tacrolimus Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide ( 7.3): Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on Olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with Olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [See Contraindications ( 4)].', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'olmesartan medoxomil and amlodipine besylate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', '•Increased exposure to cyclosporin and tacrolimus •Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide (7.3): •Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine, and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine, and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [See Contraindications (4)].', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'olmesartan medoxomil amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', '• Increased exposure to cyclosporin and tacrolimus • Increased amlodipine exposure when coadministered with CYP3A inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide (7.3): • Antidiabetic drugs: Dosage adjustment of antidiabetic may be required. Closely monitor blood pressure, renal function and electrolytes in patients on olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and other agents that affect the RAS. Do not co-administer aliskiren with olmesartan medoxomil, amlodipine and hydrochlorothiazide tablets in patients with diabetes [See Contraindications (4 )].', 'DailyMed'),
(22059, 'sucroferric oxyhydroxide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Table 1 Oral drugs that can be administered concomitantly with Velphoro Calcitriol Ciprofloxacin Digoxin Enalapril Furosemide HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors Hydrochlorothiazide Losartan Metoprolol Nifedipine Omeprazole Quinidine Warfarin Oral drugs that are to be separated from Velphoro Dosing Recommendations Doxycycline Acetylsalicylic acid Cephalexin Take at least 1 hour before Velphoro. Levothyroxine Take at least 4 hours before Velphoro Velphoro can be administered concomitantly with oral calcitriol, ciprofloxacin, digoxin, enalapril, furosemide, HMG‑CoA reductase inhibitors, hydrochlorothiazide, losartan, metoprolol, nifedipine, omeprazole, quinidine and warfarin.', 'DailyMed'),
(4674, 'sotalol hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Other No pharmacokinetic interactions were observed with hydrochlorothiazide or warfarin.', 'DailyMed'),
(4674, 'bisoprolol fumarate and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'moderate', 'Drug interactions Bisoprolol and hydrochlorothiazide may potentiate the action of other antihypertensive agents used concomitantly. Bisoprolol and hydrochlorothiazide should not be combined with other beta-blocking agents. In patients receiving concurrent therapy with clonidine, if therapy is to be discontinued, it is suggested that bisoprolol and hydrochlorothiazide be discontinued for several days before the withdrawal of clonidine.Bisoprolol and hydrochlorothiazide should be used with caution when myocardial depressants or inhibitors of AV conduction, such as certain calcium antagonists [particularly of the phenylalkylamine (verapamil) and benzothiazepine (diltiazem) classes], or antiarrhythmic agents, such as disopyramide, are used concurrently.', 'DailyMed'),
(4674, 'sotalol', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Other No pharmacokinetic interactions were observed with hydrochlorothiazide or warfarin.', 'DailyMed'),
